title: shrimp and rice au gratin
directions: Melt butter and add flour, blending well.
Add milk gradually and cook until thickened.
Add half of cheese and seasoning; cook until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Clean the shrimp and cut in half.
Mix with rice and sauce.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Dip chicken in milk and coat in mix.
Place in shallow baking pan and use a rack so fat will drain off.
Pour oleo over each piece.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stir all together and add 12 or more soda crackers, crumbled, and add 1 large can of canned milk. Put in a buttered casserole dish and cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Five minutes before it is done, put 4 slices of cheese on top and sprinkle paprika on top.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake in 3 layers until brown.
Let cool.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter or oleo and corn syrup.

Boil to hard crack stage, stirring as needed on not too hot a burner. Add baking soda and stir very well. Divide corn into 2 large pans and pour caramel mixture over corn. Stir until well coated. Place in 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with green onions, cucumbers, carrots, celery, etc.

title: fadge(potato bread)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Place potatoes in bowl and mash well.
Add egg, butter, flour and herbs. Mix well.
Add a few drops of milk if mixture is too stiff.
Shape dough into 1-inch thick round and slice into 8 pieces.
Dip in seasoned flour.
Fry on lightly greased griddle until crusty and golden on one side, 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn over and cook on other side.
Serve hot, each wedge topped with pat of butter, if desired.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: While noodles are cooking, melt butter in large skillet and saute onions until transparent.
Rinse shredded cabbage in cold water and add to onion.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and caraway seed. Cover skillet and steam until cabbage is tender.
Drain noodles and add to cabbage mixture.
Be careful not to break up noodles.
You can add diced ham or chunks of bologna to cabbage while steaming if you desire.
You can serve it as is or with sliced tomatoes for color.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Drizzle margarine on top. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Put above ingredients in crock pot and cook on low for 8 hrs.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions and mushrooms, saute until onion is done and pan juices done.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly; remove from heat.
Gradually stir in the milk.
Add bouillon cube (crumble) and thyme.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Blend in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: all-bran cake
directions: Mix the sugar, fruit, milk and all-bran together and soak overnight.
Mix altogether with the flour.
Pour in greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Chop corned beef into bite-size pieces. Add to softened cream cheese, along with green pepper, onion, sour cream, garlic salt and mushrooms. Mix thoroughly. Bake in 1 3/4-quart greased casserole for 20 minutes.

title: ben's crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream
butter;	gradually
add	sugars, beating well at medium speed
of	an electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well.; add
oil and
vanilla,
mixing well.
Combine flour, soda and salt;	add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and rest of ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten balls with tines of fork. Bake
at
325° for
minutes.	Cool
slightly; remove from cookie sheets, and cool.
Yield:
10 dozen.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: In a bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: cranberry scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Have an ungreased large cookie sheet ready. Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cranberries and sugar, then buttermilk, just until blended.
Cut dough in half.
On lightly floured surface with lightly floured fingertips, press half the dough into an 8-inch circle about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Place wedges 1/2 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until puffed and lightly browned.
Remove to rack.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 16.

title: butter crust
directions: Put butter and sugar in a bowl.
(Do not cream.)
Add flour and mix until dough forms.
Press into a 9-inch pan with well floured fingers.
Bake until golden brown at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: almond squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over first part and bake another 15 minutes.
Cut in squares like brownies when cool.

title: teriyaki hamburgers
directions: Combine soy, pineapple juice, garlic, ginger, Worcestershire and sugar.
Make 8 hamburger patties and place in plastic bag along with the pineapple slices.
Pour in marinade, seal and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain patties and pineapple reserving marinade for basting.
Grill and serve with lettuce and green pepper rings.
Serves 8.

title: piccadilly pie
directions: Crumble the crackers and mix together with pecans and baking powder; set aside.
Beat the room temperature egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Fold nut and cracker mixture into the egg white mixture and place into a well buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and pecan pieces and chill.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat well. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Add flour mixture, nuts and bananas to egg mixture. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured coffee cans or loaf pans (fill pans 1/2 full).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat 4 eggs with rotary beater.
Then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake just until a knife inserted into side of filling comes out clean.
The center may still look a bit soft, but will set later.

title: kool banana puddin
directions: Fix pudding as directed.
Add half Cool Whip.
Place wafers in bottom of glass pan.
Place layer of vanilla wafers.
Spoon pudding mixture on top.
Repeat until all is used.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with crushed wafers and bananas.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken broth, chicken, soup and mixed vegetables in bowl; mix well.
Spread in rectangular baking dish.
Spread topping evenly over top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Bring margarine and cheese to room temperature.
Combine with flour and sugar.
Drain one can apples.
Place apples that have been drained and the remaining can of undrained apples in a greased casserole dish (2 quart).
Spread the smooth topping over the apples.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with pork roast or ham.
Serves 6.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Blend wet and dry ingredients together.
Add pie filling. Bake at 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pecos corn
directions: Microwave cheese, butter and milk until melted. Drain corn and other other ingredients, and mix well into cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans in the pan.
Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring.
Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly for 7 minutes.
Immediately spread over pecans in pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips over hot mixture.
Place baking sheet over pan so chocolate will melt.
Spread chocolate over candy while hot.
Cut into squares or break into pieces when cool.
Chill when firm.

title: claire's cocoa fudge
directions: Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/4-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper; set aside.
Mix sugar and cocoa until well blended and all lumps disappear; set aside.
In a heavy, 8-cup aluminum pan, heat half and half and butter until butter melts.
Do not boil.
Add sugar-cocoa mixture to half and half, blending well.
Add corn syrup.
Place candy thermometer on side of pan, not allowing it to touch the bottom of the pan.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Keep scraping sides of the pan to remove sugar crystals.
Wash the spoon often to keep sugar crystals off.

title: orange sherbet freezer cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together in freezer can and proceed as usual for your freezer.

title: pork liver sausage (czech) jeternice
directions: Cook meat and liver until tender.
Grind meat, liver, bread and garlic.
Add seasonings.
You may add more or less according to your taste.
Add some of the broth meat and liver were cooked in. Save remaining broth.
Add water to fill kettle.
Fill casings. Tie ends and cook in remaining broth slowly for 10 minutes.
These may be frozen.
Put in shallow pan and bake at 275° for 2 hours until casing is brown.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Mash blackberries with a potato masher. Add sugar to mashed berries. Cook 1 hour. Place in hot sterilized jars.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; cool 10 minutes.
Add sugars, margarine, eggs, sifted dry ingredients and 1/2 chocolate chips. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remainder of chocolate chips and nuts (optional) on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Stir in carrot, orange rind and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices; stir into first mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: A filled butter pastry that can be made ahead, frozen and baked as needed.

title: chicken wing ding
directions: Cut wing end piece off and discard.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
In shallow pan, melt butter.
Add seasoned salt, garlic powder and tarragon.
Mix well.
In shallow pan, combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip wings, one at a time, in butter mixture, completely coating, then coat in bread crumb mixture, pressing down to coat completely.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes to an hour until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion, celery, tomato, avocado and dressing. Chill.
This may be kept in the refrigerator for several days. Just before serving, mix in the Fritos.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Brown beef and drain.
Put a spoonful of Mozzarella cheese and a spoonful of beef in shells.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, pour in spaghetti sauce.
Then add stuffed shells. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and leftover Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients over medium-low heat.
Stir constantly until it bubbles.
Mix hot mixture into dry mixture. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and cover with peanut butter, mixed with oil.
Over this, add icing.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger meat and season it to taste.
Drain meat.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes, avocado and olives.
Place in large bowl and stir in meat and crushed Doritos.
Add cheese and creamy Italian dressing.
Add 1 can of Ranch Style beans before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift
dry ingredients (first 5), then add bananas, oil, eggs, vanilla
and pineapple.
Mix all with spoon (do not beat and do not
use electric mixer).
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Pour entire batter
in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes. Frost with Butter Rum Frosting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients except potato chips. Pour into greased casserole dish and cook at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with potato chips.
Return to oven and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Drop onto greased pan about 3 inches apart.
Brown on both sides.

title: rich's hot dogs
directions: Mix currant jelly and mustard together.
Cook on low for 1 hour.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Cook until hot.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute at low heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and flour. Stir.
Drop on waxed paper on cookie tray.
Allow to cool in refrigerator.

title: hot dogs and potatoes
directions: Cut hot dogs in small pieces and set aside.
Peel and cube potatoes; cook in a frying pan on low heat so they don't stick, adding more oil if necessary.
Mince garlic and add to potatoes. When potatoes are soft, season to taste.
When potatoes are done, drain well.
Add hot dogs to pan and cook until done, adding potatoes.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: wilcox's pumpkin creation
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix in a large bowl.
Pour mixture into a large buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut margarine through dry cake mix until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Spread or sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until knife comes out dry.
Serves 12.

title: pull mints
directions: Make in very cold weather. Mix together sugar, water and butter. Add food coloring to desired color. Cook until 375° on candy thermometer. Pour quickly onto cold buttered marble slab. Add peppermint oil and flip edges over and mix together. Pick up and pull mints (outside). Must be done quickly until cool. Cut with scissors. Drop into confectioners sugar to coat. Store in tight container.

title: turkey spaghetti
directions: Cook turkey until it falls off the bone.
While deboning turkey, cook spaghetti in broth.
Mix turkey, spaghetti, peppers and onions in large pan.
Add sliced Velveeta over top of mixture.
Pour soups over top.
Add about 1/2 can of broth over top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over top and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: poached fish
directions: Stir together water, lemon juice, onion and seasonings in a large skillet.
Bring to a simmer.
Add fish; cover and adjust heat to maintain a simmer.
Cook 10 minutes per inch of thickness of thickest part of fish, probably 5 to 10 minutes.
Fish is done when it is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.
Don't overcook or it becomes tough and dry.
Serve hot with sauce or lemon juice or cold in chunks in salad.

title: peanut butter banana snack cake
directions: Mix bananas, applesauce and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Add milk and Egg Beaters; beat on high.
Add cake mix and flour.
Beat on high 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Spread frosting on cake.
Beat together remaining ingredients and drizzle over frosting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together three times. Mix oil with sugar; add eggs; add apples and pecans. Stir flour mixture in with egg mixture. Add vanilla; pour into two 9-inch cake pans. Put into cold oven. Set at 300° and bake for 45 minutes or until straw comes out clean.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix together the light brown sugar, butter, pecans and flour until crumbly.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan and pat down.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.
Let cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Wash the spinach.
Toast the pecans.
Cook the bacon.
Chop the apple.
Mix with spinach and pour the dressing over it.

title: lemon oatmeal crunch
directions: Blend together the milk and lemon juice; set aside.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream the margarine and blend in brown sugar.
Add oatmeal, cinnamon
and flour mixture. Mix with spoon or fork until crumbly.
Press all but 1/4 cup of mixture into bottom and sides of cake pan.
Pour lemon mixture into crust.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture on top of this. Bake until crust is light brown.
Cool in refrigerator before slicing and serving.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix well. Add egg; blend.
Stir soda into applesauce and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and blend.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix together margarine, flour, sugar, nuts; then spread mixture in a 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In bowl, stir together peanuts, syrup and sugar.
Microwave on High 4 minutes, stir well.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and, working quickly, add baking soda and stir until foamy and light.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet and spread thin.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: stir-fried zucchini and yellow squash
directions: Peel and mince garlic.
Wash zucchini and yellow squash and pat dry. Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: hamburgers with eggs
directions: Peel the onions; finely chop half of one and cut the other half and the second onion into rings.
Mix the chopped onion with the beef and seasoning.
Divide and shape into burgers.
Heat the oil in a skillet and fry the burgers for about 5 minutes on each side. Add the tomatoes halfway through the cooking.
Meanwhile, melt 2 tablespoons Crisco in another skillet and fry the onion rings until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add the eggs to the pan with the remaining Crisco and fry.
Top each burger with an egg; arrange on plates with the onions and tomatoes.
Sprinkle cayenne pepper on the eggs.
Fry the watercress in the Crisco; use it to garnish the burgers.

title: water chestnut and bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon strips in thirds.
Wrap each piece around chestnuts; secure with toothpicks.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bacon is crisp.
Mix together the ketchup and sugar; let sit for about 10 minutes.
Dip chestnut pieces in sauce when eating.

title: potato frank chowder
directions: Pour boiling water over hash brown potatoes.
In medium bowl, let stand 10 minutes.
Slice wieners.
Saute with onion and celery in butter in large saucepan until vegetables are tender.
Stir in celery soup, evaporated milk, salt, dill weed, potatoes and water. Heat to boiling; reduce heat and boil gently.

title: sweet freezer pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add veggies.
Put in container; set in refrigerator overnight.
Now put in small containers and freeze.

title: perfect steamed rice
directions: Put enough water over rice from when your thumb touches the rice and water hits your first joint.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to simmer and cover.
Do not lift lid for 25 minutes for simmering. Works every time.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large heavy saucepan or skillet, saute bacon or pork, until brown and crisp.
Remove.
Drain on paper towels.
Dice or crumble.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs and blend. Add flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add carrots and nuts last.
Pour into a large greased 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for several hours.
You may want to add more chili powder, salt or pepper.

title: sicilian salad
directions: Shake well. Add dressing to salad. Chill overnight. Will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: vegetable-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Melt butter in small skillet.
Add celery, carrot, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add parsley and mix well.
Place chicken breasts on squares of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle very lightly with salt and pepper.
Divide vegetables among chicken breasts, placing about 2 1/2 tablespoons in center of each.
Fold sides of breasts over mixture.
Pour 1 tablespoon white wine over each breast and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Fold foil securely over chicken to seal.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish.
Cover with Crunch Topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Boil water; add Jell-O and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemonade plus water and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Take out and let thaw for 1 hour before serving.
Break into small pieces.
Add ginger ale.
Mix until it becomes slushy.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion in skillet, stirring until beef is crumbly.
Drain.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add sour cream and cabbage; mix well.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosted punch
directions: Combine all fruit juices and sugar; still until sugar is dissolved.
Chill.
Pour into chilled punch bowl.
Stir in ice water and softened ice cream.
Serve immediately.

title: mac and cheese hot dog casserole
directions: Follow directions on macaroni and cheese.
Bring water to boil; add macaroni.
Cut up hot dogs and add to water.
Put can of corn or peas in water also.
Cook until macaroni is done; drain. Add butter; mix up.
Add milk (small amount); mix and add cheese package.
Mix well.
Great quick one-dish meal.
Enjoy!!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Cover and chill at least one hour before serving.
Serve with wheat crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Clean possum.
Scrape, clean and scald in boiling water.
Rub inside and out with salt and pepper.
Set in a cool place.
Stuff possum with chestnuts, applesauce and bread crumbs in equal proportions.
Cover with slices of sweet potatoes.
Baste with 1 cup boiling water, 1/2 cup lemon juice and 1/2 stick of butter. Baste often until tender.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Beat brown sugar, oil, buttermilk, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add to brown sugar mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.

title: fresh cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend 1 1/4 cups sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Stir in cherries and almond extract.
Cook, stir constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to boil.
Boil, stirring, for 1 minute.
Pour into 2-quart casserole, not greased, and keep hot in oven while preparing topping.

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in large bowl 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in flour. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until brown, turning once. Drain.
Serves 6.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Take out what you want to eat and mix with shredded lettuce.	Toss with mayonnaise or oil and vinegar dressing.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch width.
Mix salt and boiling water and bring to a boil.
Add 1/8 leaf slices of cabbage. Cook, covered, for approximately 25 minutes, until potatoes are done.
Add sour cream and sausage and cook 10 to 15 minutes further.
Serve.

title: pumpkin angel food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and finely chopped onion and tomato.
Mix together and sprinkle with salt, sugar and black pepper.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add vegetables and water; stir well.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add 2 cups flour sifted with spices, alternately with soda, milk and brandy.
Add fruit and nuts which have been dredged with the rest of the flour. Add beaten egg whites.
Last, drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mash beans in Armour chili and mix in hamburger along with hot dog sauce.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add Miracle Whip, water and vanilla; beat.
Bake at 350° for 45 or more minutes in 8-inch pan.

title: peanut oatmeal drops
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars gradually while mixing.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with soda and add. Stir in rolled oats and peanuts and blend thoroughly.
Form dough into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 7 minutes.

title: pineapple-banana dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 1 egg, beating 3 minutes after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Spread 2/3 of the crushed vanilla wafers into a buttered 9 x 14-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread creamed mixture over crumbs.
Top with drained pineapple; add a layer of sliced bananas.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish. Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients in a medium size mixing bowl. Spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mrs. claus' holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in 8-quart pan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine on medium speed of mixer the eggs, milk, oil, sugar and flavorings.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and poppy seed and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Before putting in oven, sprinkle 10 slivered almonds over loaves.
Drizzle honey over top when removed from oven.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add corn and tomato soup.
Simmer. Place meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole and put potatoes on top.
Dot with butter or Cheddar if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: tea cake recipe
directions: Cream together ingredients.
Add enough self-rising flour to make stiff dough.
Roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 425° until slightly brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar well with mixer.
Add eggs and beat. Alternately add dry ingredients with juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Dough will be stiff.

title: punch
directions: Mix well the first 7 ingredients.
Put in four containers and freeze.
Set out 2 hours before using.
Chip with a fork.
Add 2 bottles of ginger ale.
Add sherbet or ice cream.

title: pocket bread sandwiches
directions: Cook onion in small amount of margarine with garlic.
Add the rest of the ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Spoon into pocket bread that has been cut in half.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Mix together cottage cheese, parsley flakes, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook lasagna noodles and lay flat on wax paper.
Layer in sprayed or greased pan starting with lasagna noodles.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
While beating, add extracts.
Add flour which has been sifted 3 times slowly, alternately with small amounts of the milk.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven, adding bacon strips on top before baking.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, jello, flour, eggs and water; beat for 2 minutes.
Add the strawberries and 2 tablespoons of strawberry juice; beat for 1 minute.
Add the Wesson oil and beat for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: easy creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine over hot, not boiling water, chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla. Spread evenly in full line 9-inch pan. Chill until firm about 2 hours.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms(makes 4 servings, 4 mushrooms each)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In 12-inch nonstick skillet, melt margarine; add scallions and garlic.
Saute over medium-high heat until softened, about 1 minute.
Add crabmeat, vermouth and lemon juice; cook until crabmeat is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer to medium mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients except mushroom caps and cheese.
Mix well until thoroughly combined.

title: cauliflower balls
directions: Cook the cauliflower in water; drain. Mix the cauliflower and the cheese; form little balls. Roll the balls in flour. Beat the egg white until it is like foam. Add the yolk. Dip the balls in the egg mixture. Grind the garlic, onion and the can of tomatoes. Cook in oil. Fry the cauliflower balls and then add them to the boiling tomato mixture. Add salt to taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch glass pan. Mix other ingredients and pour over oleo.
Lay sliced peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: canned dilly beans
directions: Combine first three ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn to low and keep warm.
Put next four ingredients into a pint jar. Put syrup mixture over; put on canning lids.
Boil in cold water bath for 20 minutes.
Eat from jar just like pickles.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add tomato soup (undiluted), taco seasoning and garlic salt to taste.
Mix well and put in a low casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over this.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix both ingredients together.
Top with lettuce, chopped tomatoes, shredded cheese and black olives.
Use tortilla chips for dipping.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Stir in peanut butter to suit your taste.
Roll in small balls and cool in refrigerator.

title: pickled radishes
directions: Day Ahead:
Cut a double thickness of 5-inch square cheesecloth.
On it, place pickling spice.
Pull corners up to form a small bag and tie securely with colorfast or undyed cotton string.
In 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, heat vinegar, sugar, salt, spice bag and 3/4 cup water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix together.
Bring sugar, salad oil and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients in order given.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave squash
directions: Slice squash and onions and place in casserole dish.
Slice margarine over top and add salt and pepper.
Cover with wax paper and cook on High until desired doneness, stirring several times during cooking process.

title: orange-lemon salad
directions: Dissolve Jellos in hot water. Add cold water, add the remaining ingredients except the Cool Whip. Chill until firm. Top with Cool Whip.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg noodles.
After all other ingredients are mixed well, stir in uncooked egg noodles.
Cook at 325° for at least 45 minutes until noodles are tender.
Stir only once during cooking time.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Beat the egg; add the sugar and milk to it and use to moisten the dry ingredients.
Turn onto a well floured board; knead slightly.
Roll out, about 1-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter and cook golden brown in deep hot fat.
Drain on unglazed paper and dust with sugar.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
More mayo may be added to moisten, mixture will be thick.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pull apart cinnamon bread
directions: Cut
biscuits
in
Put
sugar and cinnamon in a bag. Shake
biscuit pieces a few at a time in the mixture and place
in Bundt
pan.
Heat
oleo
with leftover mixture plus enough sugar to fill one cup.
Boil sugar and oleo one minute. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice cheese and put evenly over top. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of cheese.
Pour melted margarine on top. Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lasagna, for filling.
Pour about 1 cup on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagna over sauce. Continue alternating layers of lasagna and filling.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake about 10 minutes longer.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before serving.
(Lasagna will expand to fill empty spaces.)

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; add milk, lemon juice and coloring.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread on pie; seal to edge.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook in large dishpan until syrup turns a good caramel color. Add corn, turn heat down to low and stir until corn is coated. Turn out to cool.
Separate in bite size pieces.

title: fried eggs and tomatoes
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a bowl; set aside.
In a large frypan, place oil and heat.
Cook tomatoes with rest of ingredients until tomatoes are cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in eggs and keep stirring until mixture thickens like scrambled eggs.
Serve over toast slices.
Serves 2 or 3 persons.

title: corn and rice salad
directions: Drain can of corn.
Combine corn, rice, pepper, onion and olives.
In screwtop jar combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce, parsley, mustard and garlic powder. Shake to mix; pour over corn mixture. Cover and chill overnight.
To serve, stir in tomatoes.
Top with cheese.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add nuts. Put in buttered pan and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: halloween charms(children's trinkets)
directions: Roll out Kooky clay with rolling pin on wax paper to 1/4-inchk thick.
With cookie cutter or knife, cut out Halloween shapes. (These are your charms.)

title: portuguese ham-kidney bean soup
directions: Cook ham in water to cover by 1 inch in 2-quart saucepan for 30 minutes or until tender.
Add beans.
Cook, covered, until beans are half-cooked.
Add tomato sauce, celery, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and cook with 1 tablespoon of oleo until vegetables are done.
Drain.
Stir in 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Pour into casserole
(2-quart).
Cut up about 3/4 pound Velveeta cheese and put on top of vegetables.
Cube 4 slices of bread and put on top of cheese.
Melt a stick of oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles and cheese melts.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar together into large bowl.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients, then add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Mix well.
Knead lightly.
Do not let rise!!!
Shape into rounds and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
25 biscuits.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix until dissolved.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve 2 yeast cakes in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add 2 beaten eggs.
Start adding flour gradually until all is used up.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning take out and knead on board.
Form into 3 little balls and put in cupcake pans.
Let raise for 3 hours in warm place covered with a damp cloth.
When raised nicely, bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush top with butter before baking.

title: cherry nut cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in walnuts and maraschino cherries.
Shape dough into a roll about 14-inches long.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap in refrigerator overnight.

title: potatoes in cream
directions: Boil potatoes until almost done.
Cool and put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, peel potatoes, slice on large side of grater.
Melt butter and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place potatoes on top, sprinkle with salt, pepper and minced onion. Pour cream over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tomato oysters
directions: Mix ingredients well, then with a tablespoon, put in the frying pan and shape into a patty.
Fry in shortening on both sides until brown.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in muffin tins at 350° until brown.

title: hamburg meat pie
directions: Mix all this in large bowl with your hands.
Roll out pie crust and fill with meat mixture.
Place top crust on and seal well. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 45 more minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples thin.
Add sugar; stir thoroughly and let stand 15 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon instant clear gel at a time, stirring thoroughly after each addition.
Pour immediately into pie crust.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: creamy pumpkin walnut fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch baking pan with aluminum foil, extending over side of pan. Grease foil. Butter sides of large heavy saucepan. Combine sugar, milk, pumpkin, butter, pumpkin pie spice and salt in buttered pan. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat. Remove from heat; add marshmallows, vanilla chips, walnuts and vanilla. Stir until dissolved. Pour into greased pan. Chill until firm. Keep refrigerated when not serving.

title: applesauce
directions: To start, wash, peel and dice apples.
Place in a medium size saucepan and add 1/4 cup of water.
Heat apples and water to a boil over medium heat.
Slowly reduce heat.
Simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to break up the apples.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Stir for 1 or 2 more minutes or until apples are done to your taste.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil ingredients for 2 minutes. Beat until thick enough to spread. Spread quickly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, place meat (cut up) on bottom.
Place vegetables over meat.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle stuffing over soup mixture.
Boil butter, seasoning packet and broth; pour over stuffing.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or microwave 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in baking dish.
Add 1 c. crushed potato chips over all.
Bake 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: black eyes of texas casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown ground beef.
Add onion, black-eyed peas, undiluted soups, enchilada sauce and garlic.
Stir.

title: broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Beat eggs with cream and cheese.
Stir in broccoli, salt, garlic powder and lemon pepper. Crumble bacon; stir in 1/2 of bacon into egg mixture.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Sprinkle top with remaining bacon.

title: mexican scrape
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning and spread on bottom of jelly roll pan.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over bean mixture.
Add salsa and garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, olives, add cheese last.
Serve with fritos or Doritos.

title: corn chowder(from marylou's soup kitchen)
directions: In a saucepan, braise onion in butter.
Add wine slowly then add both cans of corn.
Stir.
Add milk and seasonings.
Very easy but so tasty.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add pizza sauce, Hunt's sauce and 2 tablespoons Italian seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine with cooked noodles.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese and place pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is good and melted.

title: lemon chop salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Stir in salt and vinegar. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into desired mold or pan. Chill.

title: appetizer meat balls
directions: Place meat balls in sauce. Cook slowly for 1 hour. Cool and refrigerate.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together the butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Add vanilla.
Pour over Crispix.
Stir well.
In large trash bag, put the powdered sugar and cocoa.
Pour in cereal mixture, toss and mash around until it is pretty well coated.

title: oatmeal chocolate cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes. Add sugars and oleo. Stir until oleo melts. Add eggs. Mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Bake in 13 x 9-inch floured pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until done in center of cake.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in 4 portions.
Combine flour and salt; pound into meat.
Reserve remaining flour for sauce.
Brown meat in Crisco; transfer meat to shallow baking dish.
Blend reserved flour mixture into pan drippings in skillet.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrot, onion and Worcestershire sauce to drippings in skillet and cook.
Stir constantly until mixture boils.
Pour over meat. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Return to oven for a few minutes to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: With mixer cream sugar and margarine; add eggs one at a time. Add flour and
lemon flavoring.
Mix well.
Flour cherries, raisins and nuts; add to mixture. Bake in tube cake pan at 250°or 300° for approximately 2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water according to package (usually 3/4 to 1 cup water).
Put a layer of tortilla chips in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with meat mixture.
Spread warmed refried beans over the meat.
Cover refried beans with salsa.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Remove and add a layer of grated cheese.
Top with shredded lettuce and diced tomato.

title: holiday salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Toss together the apples, nuts, salt and grapes.
Fold in cranberry mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: hawaiian crown cake
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into sifter.
Stir shortening to soften.
Sift dry ingredients.
As you stir, add milk and extract.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs and yolk.
Beat 1 minute more.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch tube pan at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes. Loosen and turn right side up.

title: butter cake
directions: Put all together in mixer, mix well and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Melt chocolate chips. Add milk, vanilla, nuts and crumbs. Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
They burn easily, so watch carefully!

title: colonial cranberry salad
directions: Combine 1 cup water, sugar and cranberries in saucepan.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat, cover and let cool for 5 minutes.
Combine 1 cup boiling water and jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water, cranberry mixture and lemon juice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredietns and chill until firm.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan with margarine.
Dust with graham cracker crumbs.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until soft.
Beat in eggs, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread over top of baked cheesecake and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate to store.

title: white chili
directions: Boil chicken with water until tender.
Add broth to make nine cups.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until the flavors blend.
Serve with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and fold in flour, salt and baking powder.
Add lemon extract and pour hot water over raisins.
Let set for 2 hours, then add to cake mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken into a large glass baking dish; top with Veg-All.
Mix soups together and spread over vegetables.
Spread topping mix over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: punch
directions: Mix 8 1/2 cups water with 2 cups sugar.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Chill.
Use a 2 gallon container.
Divide.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice to each jug.
Then finish filling the jugs with water when ready to serve.
Add 1 quart ginger ale to each jug.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Makes 2 gallons or 50 punch cups.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Stir up with mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: pumpkin cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 10 x 15 x 1-inch.
Line with waxed paper.
Grease and flour the paper. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt onto wax paper.

title: busy day chicken bake
directions: Mix the rice with the soups and spread in large casserole. Brush chicken with butter; season with salt and pepper.
Arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Place onion and butter in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cook at High, uncovered, for 1 minute.
Stir in gravy, milk, broccoli, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook, covered, at High for 2 minutes; stir.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer or until broccoli is tender.
Stir in cheese.
Cover and cook at Medium (50%) for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir. Garnish with stuffing mix, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: macaroni lasagna
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse in cold running water.
Drain well.
Brown ground beef lightly; drain and cool.
In large bowl combine meat, sour cream (or Ricotta cheese), Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs.
Combine macaroni with cheese mixtures.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with part of the sauce and pour entire mixture of macaroni in dish.
Cover with generous amount of sauce and additional grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente, drain.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs. Chop well with knife and fork, form into greased 9 x 12-inch pan and a 10-inch pie plate as the crust. Cook ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and paste, sugar, water and seasonings.
Cook for about 30 minutes on low heat.
Spread sour cream on spaghetti crusts and fill with meat sauce.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
May be frozen after it is prepared and baked later.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cake in large bowl. Add layer of pudding and pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Continue to layer until ingredients are all used.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberries.
Chill before serving.

title: sarah's company chicken
directions: Break up dried beef into little pieces and layer in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Wrap each chicken filet in a strip of Sizzlean and place on top of dried beef.
Pepper- don't salt- chicken.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except rice) and pour over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Remove foil and brown, if desired.
Serve over rice.
May be prepared a day ahead.

title: chicken chips(delicious!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, sprinkling lemon juice over all. Cover with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This can be fixed ahead and frozen, leaving the cheese and chips off until time of baking.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix well together with large spoon.
Garnish with nuts, marshmallows and cherries.

title: mushroom rolled sandwiches
directions: Mix in order given.
Put teaspoonful in slice of bread.
Roll, fasten with toothpick.
If possible, place in the refrigerator overnight or for 24 hours.
Brush sandwiches with melted butter. Toast in 450 degree oven ---Serve!

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix and roll meat, rice and onion into balls; brown in skillet.
Then place into casserole dish.
In saucepan, add tomato juice or sauce with brown sugar.
Bring to boil and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Stir well and cook on medium high.
When marshmallows begin to boil, time 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and pour chocolate chips in hot syrup mixture.
Beat mixture until chips dissolve (use a wooden spoon).
Beat about 1 to 2 minutes longer and pour into buttered dish.
When cool, cut into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: 1915 ford strawberry whip
directions: Take cereal bowl.
Add Special K or cereal of your choice. Add milk and sugar.
Have side order of toast and juice, if desired.
Enjoy!!

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 11-inch quiche pan or 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
If crust becomes too dark, cover with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix everything together, but the soup.
Make patties.
Roll in flour and fry until brown.
Put in casserole and pour soup on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seasoned-crumb catfish
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, parsley and spices.
Dip fish in melted margarine. Roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange in well-greased baking dish. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°. Yield:
6 servings.

title: st. john's chicken
directions: Beat eggs well, add mayonnaise and beat.
Add egg mixture to undiluted chicken soup.
Add remaining ingredients except slivered almonds.
Grease flat casserole dish well.
Add mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Refrigerate and reheat the next day for 1 hour at 250°.
Put almonds on top before reheating.
Cut into squares and serve with the sauce.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad
directions: In a Tupperware pan, spread lettuce evenly.
Next sprinkle celery, green pepper and onion.
Spread frozen peas evenly, 2 cups mayonnaise over peas and sprinkle with the sugar and cheese.
Break up bacon and place on top.
Seal and leave overnight in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Beat egg until light.
Add sugar, salt, butter and yeast.
Beat well.
Add milk and flour alternately until the dough is smooth and stiff.
Knead well.
Put in greased bowl in warm place and cover.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Push down and allow to rise again. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet or in shallow biscuit pan covered in a warm place and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 425° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: pina colada
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until frothy.
Before serving, combine mixture with 1/2 cup crushed ice.
Yields 48 ounces.

title: cool cole slaw
directions: Finely chop green and red cabbage, grate carrot and chop onion (if desired).
Crumble Ramen into small bits.
Mix everything together.
Add dressing; mix well.
Refrigerate before eating.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cut up ingredients separately.
Place each ingredient in layers, your choice.
Pour Marie's cole slaw dressing on top. Place in refrigerator until chilled. Serve.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: In the bottom of the crock-pot, cook sauerkraut and sausage until sausage is cooked throughout.
Note:
You may need to drain some juice off your sauerkraut depending on whether or not it is vacuum packed.
Layer mashed potatoes over sauerkraut and sausage. Then add cheese and bread crumbs and cook until cheese is melted, about 15 minutes on low.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh carrots, green pepper, cucumber, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Needs no cooking; great on lettuce salad.

title: stupid pie
directions: You can substitute fruit for nuts.

title: crock-pot rice pudding
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar, water and rice.
Boil 10 minutes. Heat milk to boiling point.
Add vanilla.
Put in crock-pot on low for a few hours.
Stir every hour.
Eat hot or cold.

title: butter cookies with sprinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Let butter come to room temperature. Mix all ingredients well.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip tines of a fork in milk and press cookie down.
Bake 10 minutes.
Can be put together with preserves.

title: no crust egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer. Spray two pie tins with nonstick coating and pour mixture into pie tins. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until light brown and firm.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Simmer hamburger, onion, tomatoes and mushrooms 15 to 30 minutes with bay leaf and garlic bulb. Add mushroom soup and rice. Simmer until rice is done, covered, 10 to 15 minutes. Stuff blanched green peppers. Add 1/4 cup water to bottom of casserole dish. Bake at 350°, covered, 45 minutes. Uncover and top with shredded cheese. Bake, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: almost homemade pizza
directions: Defrost dough and raise according to package directions.
Use 1 loaf for thinner crust and 2 for thicker crust.
Knead and roll out to fit pizza pan.
Place small amount of olive oil on bottom of pan.
Add spaghetti sauce, vegetables and meat.
Top with the shredded cheese.
Add any additional ingredients (if desired) and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Enjoy!

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in Dutch oven and fry meat until brown; add onions, celery and garlic.
Stir and cook until soft.
Add Worcestershire sauce, broth and 1 stick margarine.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Season to taste.
Add rice, 1/2 cup chopped green onion tops and 1/2 cup minced parsley that has been wilted in 1/4 stick margarine.
Mix well and simmer for 2 hours.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Sift sugar and flour.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add butter, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderately hot (375°) oven 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit frosting
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, pineapple, cherries, liquid and butter. Cook until thick. Add lemon juice, nuts and coconut. Cool and spread on cake. Enough for 3-layer cake.

title: never fail soap
directions: Boil hard for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir until thick.

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease baking dish.
Put chicken into dish.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Prepare a batter of flour and milk; pour over chicken.
Warm broth and soup together; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: rich roll cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Combine and add flour, salt and vanilla.
Chill dough 3 to 4 hours (this is the secret to success!).
Roll out in 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Cut. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 60 (2-inch) cookies.

title: salsa and beef rice
directions: Brown the ground chuck. Chop it into small pieces. After it is almost done, add diced onion and let them saute and add tabasco sauce if you want to.
Boil rice according to directions on box and add to meat along with salsa, undrained tomatoes and cheese and let simmer until cheese is melted. Save a little cheese to sprinkle on top.
Serve with corn chips to dip with.

title: custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yellow squash and carrot casserole
directions: Stir margarine or butter into dressing mix.
Use half on bottom of casserole dish.
Add squash and carrots, then cream mixture.
Sprinkle rest of dressing over top.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: original bourbon chicken
directions: Cook cubed chicken until done.
In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients and cook until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Pour mixture over chicken and heat thoroughly.

title: a.1. chicken
directions: In large skillet, mix butter and Worcestershire sauce over medium heat.
Add chicken breast, salt and pepper to taste. Spread A.1. steak sauce over chicken and cover.
Cook on low to medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: my favorite cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk until a little more than pasty.
Put in eggs and oil; mix well.
Pour into a medium size iron skillet that has been oiled and placed in oven to heat. Bake at 425°.
Check at 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat egg well.
Add oil and sugar.
Gradually add zucchini. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Use loaf or tube pan.

title: angel food torte
directions: In a bowl,
combine milk, pudding and pineapple; mix well. Fold in whipped topping.
Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers. Place the bottom layer on serving plate.
Spread with 1/3 cup of pineapple mixture.
Repeat with next layer.
Place top layer on cake.
Spread with remaining pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with a ring of cherries.
Serves 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs, then add the milk, corn, oil, pimentos, onion, jalapeno, salt, garlic and cornmeal.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake for 1 hour or until set at 350°.
On removal from oven, sprinkle with 2 cups grated cheese.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple. Place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix cheese, sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pineapple. Top with Ritz crackers. Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until drops of icing form a soft ball when dropped in cool water.
Remove from heat and let cool.
If icing becomes too stiff, add a tablespoon of milk and heat slightly.

title: oatmeal-applesauce walnut bread(this is a low-fat bread.)
directions: Combine brown sugar and egg in a large bowl, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in applesauce. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Gradually add to egg mixture, stirring to blend.
Add 1 1/2 cups oats, raisins, walnuts and oil; stirring well.

title: hot relish
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Put on medium heat to boil, about 2 minutes.
Lower heat.
Pack into hot sterilized jars.
Seal with hot, sterilized lids and rings.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix jello according to box directions. Mix in sour cream and Cool Whip until uniform.

title: bird's nest pudding
directions: Pare and core apples and place in baking dish.
Fill centers with 1/2 cup sugar packed firm.
Make a custard of milk, beaten eggs and 1 cup of sugar.
Pour over apples and grate plenty of nutmeg over top.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut cooked chicken
into
large bite-size pieces.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Combine
soups
and
sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Mix Ritz
crumbs with melted margarine. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dried apple pies
directions: Cook apples until done.
Drain well and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Use biscuit or make own dough; roll out a small circle.
Fill with apples.
Fold over and press together with fork.
Fry in a large skillet.

title: nacho cheese chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef, pepper and onion until lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain fat from pan.
Stir in milk, soup, corn, diced tomato and cheese spread.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 5 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with tortilla chips or can be used as a dip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan with 1/4 edge up sides.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake about 25 minutes longer or just until no imprint remains when touched lightly in center.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: idaho cups with white cheddar and herbed duchess potatoes(serves 6)
directions: You will need a deep fryer or casserole pan with oil to cover and a pastry bag.

title: darn good chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. Mix cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large mixing bowl. Blend on low speed 1 minute, then on medium speed for 3 minutes more. Fold in chocolate chips. Spoon into Bundt pan and bake for 58 to 62 minutes. Then place on wire rack to cool for 30 minutes.

title: old country stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine beef, pork, salt, pepper, rice and onion with 1 can of tomato sauce.
Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain.
Divide mixture of meat onto center of each leaf. Roll up, tucking ends in securely.
Brown in hot oil.
Mix remaining can tomato sauce with brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over rolls; simmer, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add next 7 ingredients to drippings; cover and cook 10 minutes, turning cabbage once.
Add sausage; cover and cook 5 minutes or until sausage is heated.
Transfer to serving dish with slotted spoon and sprinkle with bacon.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Stir to mix well.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes or to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter and stir vigorously.
Pour icing over yellow sheet cake.
Let set to allow icing to harden.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and add chili powder (put aside).
Cook package of spaghetti; saute bell pepper and celery.
Add it to spaghetti sauce.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of spaghetti, layer of meat and layer of sauce, with cheese on top.
Repeat layers with the last layer being cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°; cook until cheese is melted.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast into hot water; add salt, sugar and olive oil. Add to hot water the flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Put in warm place for 1 hour.
Roll out.
Use the topping and sauce of your choice.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: navy carrots
directions: Cut carrots into long strips, julienne style.
Add sugar to water and boil carrots for 15 minutes.
Saute onion in butter and place in baking dish.
Add carrots and salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 400° until tender.

title: spicy zucchini drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl sift together dry ingredients and add this to the first mixture.
Stir in zucchini and milk.
Mix well and add nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degree for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach and orzo salad
directions: Boil orzo slowly until slightly overdone.
Coat pan with extra virgin oil.
Add garlic and start to brown.
Add pine nuts; toast. Add spinach.
Add kosher salt, cayenne and black pepper.
Cool spinach mixture.
Combine with orzo and Romano cheese.
Garnish with Romano cheese.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together.
Mash them up real good and add eggs, then add salt and pepper.
Cook a few more minutes, then taste.
Pour into a bowl.
Add cheese, crushed crackers and mayonnaise.
Mix together, then pour into a casserole dish and bake for 15 minutes at 300°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin, water and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into a bowl and chill until thickened.
To hasten chilling, place bowl of pudding mixture in larger bowl of ice and water, then stir until thickened.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and chill until set, 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and strawberries.

title: strawberry banana yogurt pops
directions: In food processor, combine all ingredients and pulse until smooth. Pour mixture into 8 plastic ice-pop holders or 8 small Dixie cups. Place wooden ice cream sticks in each cup's center. Freeze for 4 hours.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease the bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom.
Thoroughly combine berries with dry jello; set aside.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and vanilla flavoring with the cream cheese.
Add sugar, flour, salt and eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Do not overbeat; just beat until it is creamy.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
This is a good breakfast cake.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add raisins, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: lemon coconut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with lemon juice and vanilla, mixing well after each addition.
Chill dough.

title: perfect pasta salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti or linguine as label directs; drain.

title: macaroni tuna salad(serves 350+ people)
directions: Cook macaroni and cool.
Cook and peel eggs.
Drain tuna, chop onions, celery and carrots.

title: hot or cold gazpacho soup
directions: Hot: Combine ingredients in a 5-quart crock-pot and heat for several hours. Stir occasionally.

title: clay
directions: Knead together and let set in cool place overnight.

title: christmas cake
directions: Weeks or days before baking:
Wash and grind or blend all fruits together in blender.
Place blended fruits in glass bottle or jar with rum and wine; mix well and let stand, covered tightly. Use only enough liquor to cover fruits.

title: pecans
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix pecan halves with butter.
Toss to coat thoroughly.
Spread in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cool*.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: pine cone dip
directions: Beat cheese until softened and add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Mold into pear shape and start at the bottom placing almonds in rows.
Garnish with pine or parsley sprigs.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Chill overnight.
Peel and grate potatoes. Combine with next 6 ingredients and half the cheese in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together ice cream, Cool Whip and peanut butter. Pour into crust and freeze.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add canned tomatoes, tomato soup and kidney beans to pan and simmer for 10 minutes. Mix salt, chili powder, flour and water in a measuring cup. Stir and make a paste, then add to pan and simmer for 45 minutes. Also, add 2 dashes of garlic powder. Cook uncovered.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 inch deep oil to 375°.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Mash squash.
Add all, except last 2, ingredients; mix well.
Mix butter and crumbs.
Put squash mixture over crumbs.
Top with the rest of crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: milk chocolate frosting
directions: To make frosting, combine sugar, milk and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until small amount dropped in water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; add chocolate pieces and Marshmallow Creme, stirring until melted.
If necessary, add a small amount of milk to spread well.

title: kettle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients together and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: glazed fruited chicken
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 2/3 cup liquid; set aside.
Stir reserved liquid into mayonnaise; stir constantly over medium heat until mixture boils.
Add stuffing and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Brush with additional mayo.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Melt marmalade. Arrange fruit around chicken.
Brush on marmalade.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.
Serves 50.

title: auntie jill's candy logs
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar, dates and eggs.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies; mix gently.
Coat 2 pieces of waxed paper with confectioners sugar. Turn 1/2 of mixture onto each piece of waxed paper.
Roll up; shape into logs with palms of hands.
Chill; cut into slices.

title: southern-style black-eyed peas
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain and place in crock-pot. Add water and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high for 1 to 2 hours, then turn to low for 8 to 9 hours.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: homemade chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in cream over low heat.
Add sugar and salt. Take off heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir constantly until cooled.
Yields 1 cup sauce.

title: helen's eccles cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out half of pastry and fit it in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Roll out remaining pastry to the same size and place on a baking sheet.
Bake both crusts about 12 minutes until browned.
Cool.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, butter, cinnamon, salt, currants and water in a heavy pan and cook until thickened.
Pour mixture into pan with crust on the bottom. Top with second crust.
Sprinkle with a little water and sprinkle with sugar.
Refrigerate before cutting into squares with a sharp knife.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: mexican party mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix margarine and seasoning.
Pour over combined remaining ingredients, except cheese balls; toss to coat.

title: burgundied meatballs
directions: In large bowl, mix well the first 6 ingredients; shape mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook meatballs, a few at a time, until well browned on all sides.
With slotted spoon, remove them to plate as they brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, bran, honey, salt and soda; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients to moisten.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan, filling 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: zesty ham roll-ups
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and mustard.
Add green onions and mix well.
Spread about 1/4 cup cream cheese mixture on each tortilla to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Cover each with 2 to 3 spinach leaves, pressing lightly into cream cheese mixture.
Top with 1 to 2 bell peppers and 2 slices of ham.
Keep layers as flat as possible.
Roll up tightly in jelly roll fashion.
Wrap each securely in parchment paper or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate, seam- side down, at least
1 hour.
Remove wrapping; discard.
Cut each roll crosswise into 1 - inch slices.
Serve on lettuce lined platter.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Combine vegetables and toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra.
Pack 1 pepper and 1 clove garlic in pint jar. Combine salt, vinegar and water; boil.
Pour over okra.
Wait 30 minutes; pour off.
Reheat.
Pour back in jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix flour and sugar; add to eggs.
Add other ingredients in order.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Do not prick crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 50 minutes, until pie is firm in center.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add broth from the chicken or turkey.
Add cream of chicken soup (have all the lumps creamed out) and 1 cup of water.
Boil until all the ingredients are smooth. Mix with the dry ingredients and put in a large container and set in the refrigerator until the next morning.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter in your baking pan and add the dressing.
Bake at 375° until the top is golden brown.
Good for Christmas supper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla, and 1/3 cup of the butter. Mix well. Spoon into a 2 quart casserole dish.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Use can of biscuits.
Cut out centers and fry.
Put in bag of cinnamon and sugar, then shake up.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake 3 white cake layers.
Cool.
Slice crosswise to make 6 layers.
Stack and spread each layer with cut side up with:

title: tomato-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, onions, garlic, parsley, oil, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Makes 6 (3/4 cup) servings.
Contains 145 calories per serving.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart container (add vinegar last). Seal; shake thoroughly.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1 package ham).
Chill, roll into ball.
Roll ball in second package of ham.

title: congealed salad
directions: Fix Dream Whip by directions.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine pineapple and sugar; add to jello.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cheese.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Trim fat from chicken; melt fat in large, heavy kettle or Dutch oven.
Brown chicken, a few serving size pieces at a time; drain on paper toweling.
Fry bacon lightly in same kettle; remove and set aside.
Pour off all fat.
Return browned chicken and bacon to kettle; add onion, salt, peppercorns and water.
Cover tightly; heat to boiling, then simmer 2 hours or until chicken is tender. (If much fat has cooked out, remove the kettle from heat; let stand 5 to 10 minutes, then skim off all fat.)
Reheat to boiling; stir in macaroni and parsley flakes.
Add 1 cup of water, if needed. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 14 to 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Season to taste with salt if needed.

title: chicken stroganoff casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large pan and brown chicken breasts lightly, about 4 minutes, remove breasts from pan to a baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches).

title: spiced pickled peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water; add boiling water and 1 cup peach juice to Jell-O and gelatin, then let set until soft consistency.
Add all other ingredients and put into 1-quart mold or 8 to 10 individual molds.

title: spanish style pork roast
directions: Cut a few slits
in
fat
side
of roast, then rub roast with salt and
pepper.
Place garlic in slits and sprinkle with allspice and thyme.
Place
meat on rack in shallow pan; sprinkle with oil.
Roast
at
350° until meat thermometer registers 170°. It will take 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine milk and water, add pudding mix, beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 2-1/2 qt. glass bowl put a layer of wafers, a layer of bananas and a layer of pudding mixture.
Do that 3 times.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a dishpan or very large mixing bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining
ingredients,
except pecans. Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: broccoli with rice casserole
directions: Cook Broccoli until it is tender.
In a medium casserole dish put broccoli, rice, soup and 1 c. of water.
Stir until it is mixed good.
Add butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and add Cheese Whiz and French fried onions on top.
Bake for another 15 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix the salad dressing and soy sauce together; pour over the chicken wings.
Marinate for 1 to 2 days.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste the chicken periodically.
When the chicken is cooked, drain the marinade and place chicken under the broiler until crispy.
Turn so both sides are crispy.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, nuts, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Let cool.

title: buttermilk delight
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add Jell-O and heat until dissolved.
Set to cool.
Add buttermilk and let set again until jelled.
