Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.

title: marinated italian garlic chicken
directions: Mix dressing and seasonings.
Pour dressing mixture over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate 20 minutes.
Drain.
Place chicken on grill or greased broiler pan.
Grill on broil for 10 to 12 minutes on each side or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Sift together sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Scald milk in double boiler.
Add dry ingredients.
When mixture begins to thicken, add 1/2 cup to egg yolks, then pour back into mixture. Stir very often, cooking until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut; stir until butter melts.
Pour into pie shell.
Spread meringue on hot filling, sealing to edge of crust.
Bake in 350° oven until light golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, two at a time; beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: creamy butter bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg.
Press on cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese, egg and powdered sugar; pour over pressed mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Use to dip fruit or as a fruit salad dressing.
Especially good with apple slices.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Fill cupcake papers 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Add favorite topping or pie filling.
(I use cherry pie filling.)

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel cucumber; cut lengthwise into quarters.
Remove seeds. Slice into thin strips.
Soak in ice water for 15 minutes; drain and pat dry.
Spread flattened slices of bread with mayo or cream cheese.
Cover with overlapping strips of cucumber.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Trim crust and slice into finger strips.

title: helen's chocolate chip (or else) cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla. Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix until blended; do not overmix.

title: oh-so-garlicky bread
directions: Heat broiler or grill.
In bowl, combine peppers, basil, oil and cheese.
Place bread, cut side up, on rack 4-inches from heat source (or cut side down on grill over medium coals); toast 3 minutes or until golden.
Rub with garlic; top with pepper mixture and return to broiler 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut crosswise into 8 pieces.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Scald milk.
Beat egg yolks and add milk slowly.
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook over hot water in a double boiler until mixture coats a spoon.
Add dissolved gelatin to hot custard mixture.
Chill until thick.
Add egg whites, 1/2 cup sugar, Macadamia nuts and rum flavoring and fold into chilled custard mixture.
Turn into a baked pie shell.
Chill.
To serve, top with whipped cream sprinkled with chopped Macadamia nuts.

title: smothered cajun chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce, salt and hot sauce for 2 or 3 hours.
In a large skillet or Dutch oven, put oil, onion, pepper and garlic and saute until tender.
Add parsley and white wine to chicken.
Marinate and add water.
Cover and cook slow 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pork in cider sauce
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown pork in hot oil; drain off fat.
Add 1/2 cup of the cider and the onion.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 40 minutes, or until meat is tender.
In a bowl, combine cornstarch, brown sugar, salt and vinegar.
Add to pork mixture, along with chopped apple. Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Add vanilla and butter extract.
Combine baking soda and flour; add alternately with buttermilk beginning and ending with flour. Add bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch loaf pans at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: potatoes pittsburg
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into greased casserole dish. Bake at 400° until potatoes are tender.

title: oats 'n' pumpkin pinwheels
directions: Beat 1 cup sugar and margarine until fluffy; mix in egg whites. Stir in combined flour, oats and baking soda.
On wax paper, press into 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread combined pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar and spice over dough to 1/2-inch from edge.
From narrow end, roll up dough.
Sprinkle sesame seed around roll, pressing gently. Wrap in waxed paper; freeze overnight or until firm.
Heat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut frozen dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake on cookie sheet 9 to 11 minutes or until golden.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.

title: beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix and form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chicken and scalloped vegetable casserole
directions: Steam vegetables for 5 minutes. Drain.
Melt butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.

Gradually add milk and simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Remove from heat. In 1-quart casserole, alternate vegetables and sauce. Place chicken pieces around edges of casserole and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 55 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except potatoes. Mix well.
Fold in potatoes to cheese mixture.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking sheet lightly with vegetable oil.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix by hand until well combined.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place on baking sheet.
Bake until firm to the touch, approximately 40 minutes.
Cut into slices and serve with a mushroom gravy.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add soup, cheese, onion rings and tomatoes.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour in casserole dish. Place Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and milk.
Let come to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Then add oatmeal, cocoa and vanilla. Mix until thickens, then drop on cookie sheet.

title: "king ranch" casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together in a large skillet.
Add all the cans and cook until bubbly.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a large casserole.
Lay 1/2 of the tortillas across the mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the cheese across the tortillas.
Pour rest of the mixture on top of the cheese.
Lay the rest of the tortillas across the mixture.
Sprinkle all of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together; refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: sweet and sour beef cabbage soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine all ingredients except flour and oil. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and oil until well blended; stir into the soup.
Simmer until slightly thickened.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Make a roux of the flour and oil; cook until dark brown.
Add chopped seasoning and saute until limp.
Add raw shrimp and continue stirring until pink.
Add cut up tomatoes and 3 quarts water.
Add corn, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 10.

title: easy pear loaf
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour over melted butter in pan.
Put pears on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes and mash while hot.
Let cool for 20 minutes. Add everything remaining, stir and chill.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add hot water and sugars; cool slightly.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix this mixture into the cream mixture.
Divide dough into 3 circles about 1/3-inch thick.
Place on a greased baking sheet and prick with a fork.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cut into wedges while still warm, but do not remove from sheet until cold.
Makes approximately 24 cookies.

title: s'more cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, graham cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture, beating until blended.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Take the
macaroni
and
cheese,
pour	it
all
into a medium-sized cooking
dish	and work it all up together.
Then beat up eggs.
Add	a
little
sweet
milk to the macaroni you already have in
the
dish.
Grate	quite
a bit of cheese and stir it all
up real well, then put some more grated cheese on top of the contents in the dish.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter, egg and milk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir into mixture.
Place dough on lightly floured wax paper. Roll in a rectangle.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cool slightly and spread over dough.
Roll up dough like a jellyroll; lift wax paper slightly at each turn.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes (not too long, or chocolate will break when slicing).
Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: main dish casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes. Mix in corn and pimentos and mushrooms.
Cook noodles and drain.
In large casserole dish, layer noodles, vegetables and meat sauce.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make into large roll or 2 small rolls.
Roll in wax paper.
Store in icebox until ready to use.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 7 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately until done.
Mix together. Add cheese and both soups.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: fruit krisp (frozen dessert)
directions: Thaw berries.
Add other ingredients.
Freeze in individual dishes.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: toll house heart-shaped pan cookie(makes one large cookie)
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat in egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup morsels; spread into greased and wax paper-lined 8 1/2 or 9-inch heart-shaped pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
No water. In 8 x 12-inch pan, spread beans evenly.
Layer meat and green chilies, sprinkle cheese over and spoon salsa over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, onions and broccoli.
Mixing well, add 1 stick melted butter.
Pour in well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gooey pecan bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter.
Press into bottom of a lightly-greased, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour or cornstarch in a large saucepan. Gradually add milk and butter, while stirring. Cook to desired consistency. Serve over biscuits or pancakes.

title: waldorf salad(cole slaw)
directions: In medium bowl, combine cabbage, apple, celery and nuts.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and chill 4 hours to blend flavors.

title: hot mustard dip
directions: Shake vinegar, mustard and sugar together for 20 minutes.
Add beaten eggs and shake for an additional 5 minutes. Cook mixture in double boiler until thick.
Makes 1 pint.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, oil and eggs.
Add 7-Up.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Use confectioners sugar icing and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until partially tender.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add soup and milk.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Next, add broccoli and rice.
Cook in a greased baking dish for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter and cream cheese. Add milk, lemon juice and cool whip. Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in salt and spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients in a small bowl until well blended.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spicy black bean and corn salsa
directions: 1. Mix first 7 ingredients in large bowl.

title: apricot almond squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cake mix and 1/2 cup margarine and mix until crumbly. Stir in almonds.
Reserve 1 cup and pat rest into bottom of pan. Carefully spread 1 cup of apricot preserves over crust (for easy spreading, heat).
Beat all other ingredients except coconut and reserved crust until blended.
Spread over apricot preserves. Combine coconut and crust mix and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and center is set. Cool completely and store in fridge.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup berries.
Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch, crushed berries and water.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Put 3 cups berries in cooled pie shell.
Pour cooled sauce over them.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with several berries.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cauliflower ham chowder
directions: Cook cauliflower in chicken broth in a large covered saucepan until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
In a mixing bowl, gradually stir cream into potato soup.
Blend water, cornstarch and pepper. Stir into potato mixture.
Pour over cauliflower and cook, stirring often, until thick and bubbly. Stir in ham; simmer over low heat for 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese with electric mixer until creamy.
Beat in eggs, evaporated milk and red pepper.
Stir in spinach, ham and onion.
Pour into frozen pie crust, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a baking sheet, 50 to 60 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Stir (do not beat).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: ruth's salad(diabetic)
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, Cool Whip, cottage cheese and mandarin oranges together well. Then sprinkle dry Jell-O over this and mix well.
Chill.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough and cut into 8 slices.
Cut each slice into thirds.
Put pieces into greased Bundt pan.
Mix pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans together.
Spread mixture over top of bread slices.
Cut up butter and drop around on top. Cover with dish towel and let set on counter all night.

title: lil's never fail fudge
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
butter together.	Meanwhile, beat eggs; add vanilla
and mix in powdered sugar.
When butter and chips are melted (bubbly hot), add to egg and sugar; mix well. Add 1 cup chopped
nuts
if
desired.
Pour
into
a	buttered 9-inch square dish.
Cut into squares.
May be frozen.

title: spicy chili and tortilla strips
directions: Add hamburger meat, corn, other vegetables and potatoes to tomato puree and tomato paste.
Add picante sauce and Ro-Tel sauce. Simmer until it has cooked down slightly.
Serve in bowl with shredded cheese sprinkled on top.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a full boil over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large, glass dish.
Pour vinegar mixture over sauerkraut mixture.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
This will keep for 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Very good with pork dishes or as a relish on hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: chicken dish
directions: Cook rice as per directions on box.
Combine the ingredients and bake for 50 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Serves eight.

title: macaroni bake casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine meat, onions, green pepper, peas, milk and beaten eggs in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Add macaroni.
Last add powdered cheese packet.
Stir and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can save some of powdered cheese to garnish top of casserole.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Fill with thin layers of chili beans, onion and corn chips.
Have chili on the top layer. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until heated and browned.
Serves 4.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix all
together
and chill in refrigerator.
Children love to help make this!

title: minted carrots
directions: Heat butter, honey and mint in saucepan until butter melts. Add carrots and simmer for about 8 minutes until carrots are glazed.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients well.
Sift the dry ingredients 3 times and add to the first mixture.
Add the apples and pecans. Bake in a prepared 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickled okra
directions: Put cloves of garlic in bottom of jars, then pack okra.
Bring to boil the vinegar, water and spices and pour over okra.
Seal jars and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Excellent for marinating steaks.

title: party meat ball (barbecue)
directions: Mix all together.
Form small meat balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: high speed beef
directions: Bake venison, onion and water until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
After baking, remove all grease from meat juices.
Cool.

title: cream cheese chip dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and salsa in pot over medium heat on stove.
Stir until cheese is melted and mixed with salsa.
Grab your favorite bag of chips and enjoy.

title: chocolate pick-me up cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, chocolate chips and coconut; sprinkle on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix well the oleo, sugar and flour.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 375°; cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well.
Prepare Dream Whip and combine with cheese mix.
Spread over crust.
Spread pie filling over cheese mix.
Chill.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice.
Mix other ingredients with rice.
Bake 1 hour at 325° with lid on Pyrex bowl.
Freezes well.
(You can cut this in half.)

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut up celery, onions, carrots and cabbage.
Bring water to boiling and add ingredients, except rice.
Cover and boil slowly for 15 to 20 minutes, until vegetables are almost tender.
Add rice.
Lower heat and cook about 25 minutes longer until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings, 1 cup each.

title: mawmaw brumley's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with milk and vanilla to cream mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pans and bake in a moderate 350° oven until tests done.
If butter is used, omit salt.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: italian sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 4 hours.
Meatballs can be made of hamburger, onion and garlic and added to sauce to simmer.

title: chocolate-covered pretzels
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, combine chocolate morsels, corn syrup, shortening and water.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat but keep mixture over hot water.
Dip pretzels into mixture to coat evenly.
Place pretzels on wire rack.
Chill in refrigerator until coating sets.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature until surface dries (about 1 hour).

title: white angel pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in cornstarch.
Blend to a smooth consistency with small amount of water. Cook until thick and clear, preferably in double boiler.
Add salt to egg whites. Beat until stiff. Add sugar and vanilla, beating until creamy.
Pour cornstarch mixture over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Spread whipped cream over pie and sprinkle with chocolate shavings.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat.
Add cinnamon, ginger, baking powder, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir.
Add pumpkin.
Mix. Add flour.
Mix.
Drop by tablespoons and bake at 350° until done.

title: creamy potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup cheese, 3 tablespoons green onion, skim milk, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir into potatoes.
Put into 2-quart shallow 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes. Sprinkle on green onions.
Serves 10.

title: herbed leg of lamb
directions: In a small bowl, mash salt and garlic to a paste.
Stir in oil, lemon juice and seasonings.
Place lamb on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Rub entire surface with herb mixture.
Roast at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes per pound, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until meat thermometer registers 175° to 180°; baste often.
Stand 5 to 10 minutes before carving.

title: ranch house "chickenchilada"
directions: Combine soups, onion and wine together.
In an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch greased Pyrex baking dish, layer the tortillas, cream mixture, peppers, cheese and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant scallopini
directions: Heat butter and oil in large skillet.
Add onions, garlic, 1/2 tsp. salt and bay leaf.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add eggplant, 1/2 tsp. salt; stir and cook covered 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, spices, peppers, tomatoes and paste.
Mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add Marsala and parsley, cover and simmer 15-20 minutes.
Just before serving mix in parmesan.
Serve over pasta.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallow and stir until completely melted.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Using butter spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in skillet until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except buns.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill buns with meat.

title: homemade pie crust
directions: Mix flour and lard together until consistency of corn meal. Mix egg, water, vinegar and salt together and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured board.
Mixture will be soft, but easy to manage.
Makes two 9-inch pies.
Fill with favorite fruit filling.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Dice cucumber.
Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Store in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: baked stew
directions: Place vegetables in a large casserole and pour oil over them. Bake 45 minutes in a 400° oven.
Stir 3 to 4 times to keep vegetables coated with oil.
During this time put mushroom soup in a pan; dilute with juice from dinner cuts and 1/2 cup water.
Cut dinner cuts in 1-inch cubes and add to vegetable mixture.
Stir well and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until vegetables are done. Salt may be added as desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion; drain.
Mix in soup and soy sauce.
This much can be done and refrigerated until ready to bake.
Add noodles, but save some for topping, mixed vegetables and mushrooms.
Place in a large casserole dish or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Mix remaining ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or in pastry shells.
Serves 4.

title: whipping cream icing
directions: Heat flour and milk until a paste.
Cream margarine and Crisco. Add to flour mixture.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Looks like whipped cream.
Store in cool place (refrigerate).

title: lou's seasoning
directions: Mix well and use like salt.
I use this also to boil crawfish. Use on all meats, seafoods and poultry.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook
and
drain broccoli.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine
broccoli,
onion, eggs, cottage cheese, salt and cornbread mix.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: peach delight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 round pans.
Drain peaches, reserving juice. Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups. Prepare cake mix, using juice instead of water.
Bake and cool as directed.
Cut peaches into bite size pieces.
Mix yogurt and whipped topping.
Fold in peaches.
Fill layers with half of the peach mixture.
Spoon remaining peach mixture over top of cake. Refrigerate 2 hours or until chilled.

title: holiday cake
directions: Cream margarine, cheese, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift 2 cups flour with baking powder and add slowly to creamed mixture. Combine remaining 1/4 cup flour with cherries and 1/2 cup pecans. Fold into batter.
Sprinkle remaining pecans into bottom of a well greased (no flour) tube pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then remove to finish cooling.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour with spices.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add molasses and vinegar.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add more flour to make soft dough.
Roll out on floured board.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 100.

title: better homes and gardens cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Cook spinach and onion according to package directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
In a bowl, combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, margarine and garlic powder.
Stir in spinach and muffin mix.
Cover and chill 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Cover and chill until serving time.
(Or place in a freezer container; seal, label and freeze.)

title: truffles
directions: Melt milk chocolate in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
When melted, beat until smooth.
Meanwhile, combine heavy cream and half and half in small saucepan; heat to scalding.
Remove from heat; let stand until temperature is about 130°.
Add warm cream to melted chocolate at once.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and let cool.
When cool, beat with electric mixer until candy is light and rather fluffy.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.
When firm, roll a teaspoonful of candy into a ball in palms of hands.
Dip immediately into melted chocolate with dipping fork and place on wax paper to dry.
When ready to package, use small candy cups for each individual piece.
Makes 36 to 40 (2 pounds).

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with water to egg mixture.
Stir in kraut.
Bake in 2 large pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: instant cheese soup
directions: Combine with 3 cans of milk, Velveeta cheese, garlic powder and Tabasco sauce.
Cook over medium heat and stir often until cheese is completely melted.
Takes about 20 minutes if you cube your cheese into 2-inch squares.

title: spinach and tomato quiche
directions: Line an ungreased pie plate with crust, fluting edges as desired.
Do not prick crust.
Set aside.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot dog bacon bundles
directions: Cut hot dogs, bacon slices and cheese slices in half.
Fry bacon until done, but not real crisp.
Wrap half slice bacon and half slice cheese around half hot dog.
Flatten biscuit.
Lay wrapped hot dog in center of flattened biscuit.
Pull edges up around and pinch together.
Stick toothpick through to keep from coming open while baking.

title: peanut butter chocolate candy cookies(with wooden spoon)
directions: Mix together; put this mixture on a well greased cookie sheet and pour over it a 12 ounce bag of melted chocolate morsels. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Remove.
Slice into squares.
Leave in pan and put back into refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt the butter in large frying pan or Dutch oven.
Add the onions and place the chicken over onions.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Peel and chop tomatoes, then combine with paprika and stir lightly.
Cook 10 minutes.
Mix cream with soda and pour over chicken.
Cook for another 35 minutes.
Remove chicken, strain the sauce and pour over chicken.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Combine and pour over chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix together pineapple, strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Spread 1 1/2 cups cheese over croutons in 9 x 13 pan. Spread browned and drained sausage over cheese. Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard together and pour over top of mixture in pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cinnamon candy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add candy to 1/2 cup boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add to dissolved jello and cool until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into individual molds or ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: garden club turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients the night before using, except pineapple. Use deli style turkey (buy in chunk and cut up or use leftover turkey).
Canned pineapple can be used.
Be sure to drain very well!!!
Serves 4.

title: judy and sue's cranberry jello salad
directions: *Grind in food processor or equivalent.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend in blender until creamy.
Cool and pour over spinach, mushrooms, boiled eggs and cooked bacon.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: easy caramels
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add Karo; mix.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add condensed milk.
Bring to a boil again.
Boil 12 to 15 minutes or 234°.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix oil and sugar, add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses. Sift in dry ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls and dip in sugar. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Place 3/4 of the mix in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on crumbs.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on ice cream.
Place in freezer.
Cut in squares and serve with a cherry.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, soup, olives, green chilies and sour cream.
Add 1/2 cup enchilada sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Spread mixture evenly in each tortilla. Roll.
Continue procedure with each tortilla.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with remaining enchilada sauce.
Spread Jack cheese evenly over enchiladas.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.
Serve with refried beans and small salad.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the box.
Add evaporated milk to cake mix.
Bake half of batter for 15 minutes.
While waiting, unwrap caramels and place in a heavy saucepan.
Add 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
On medium heat, melt caramels.
Pour caramel sauce on cake that was baked, spread chocolate chips evenly over this and place pecan halves on this.
Pour on remaining batter and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chew bread or brown brownies
directions: Cream all of the ingredients together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Mix as listed and chill.

title: sweet and sour dressing or dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate before using.

title: summer tea
directions: Steep boiling water and tea bags for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Wash and salt chops.
Dunk in flour on both sides.
In a pan, put about 1/2 cup oil.
Heat.
Take floured chops and brown on both sides, one by one.
When all 12 chops are browned, put them all back in pan.
Add about 1 cup water and put lid on.
Turn heat to low and simmer them until done.
Add more water if necessary. Saute onion in about 1/4 cup oil.
Add salt, paprika and black pepper.
If you wish, add 1 red pepper, diced, and some chopped parsley leaves.
Now add 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Stir; it will be like a sauce.
Add a beef bouillon.
Put the clean, sliced mushrooms in and with low heat, cook until almost done, about 1/2 hour.
At the end, take 1 tablespoon flour and put in a cup.
Fill up with water while stirring so no lumps will occur.
Take flour and water and pour in mushrooms to thicken sauce.
Cook for a little while.
Remove pork chops from pan and pour mushroom sauce over it.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: south carolina red rice
directions: Cook
bacon.
Remove from pan and crumble.
Cook onions in bacon fat until tender.
Add rice, tomatoes, seasonings and crumbled
bacon.
Cook
on low heat about 35 minutes, stirring well.
Stir
with
fork
several
times
while cooking.
Check after 15 minutes and add water, if needed.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: baklava
directions: Combine almonds, sugar and cinnamon.
Place 8 sheets of phyllo (one at a time) in bottom of 8 x 14 x 2-inch pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Sprinkle generously with nut mixture.
Place 2 butter sheets of phyllo on top.
Sprinkle with nut mixture; add 2 butter sheets.
Continue layering nut mixture and phyllo dough until all nut mixture is used.
Place remaining phyllo sheets on top, buttering each sheet before placing in pan.
With a sharp knife, cut Baklava into small diamond shapes.
Place a pan of water on lower shelf in preheated 300° oven.
Bake Baklava on middle shelf for 3 hours, making sure water pan is always full.
Remove from oven and pour cool syrup over pastry.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain excess fat.
Add chopped onion, taco seasoning, Ro-Tel tomatoes and salsa to meat.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pam oblong baking dish.
Divide number of flour tortillas it will take to cover mixture in dish.
Spread cream cheese on tortillas, using whole package of cheese.
Spread 1/2 meat mixture in dish.
Cover with cheese topped tortillas, cheese side up. Sprinkle with olives and green chiles.
Cover with additional tortillas.
Cover with rest of meat mixture.
Sprinkle liberally with Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve with chips.

title: tortoni
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except whipped cream; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fill 2 1/2-inch foil cups; cover.
Or put in fancy glass bowl.
Cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.

title: taffy candy
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, butter and vinegar.
Cook, constantly stirring slowly until mixture reaches 260° or candy hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour into greased pan or platter. When cool enough to handle, butter hands and pull until light golden color.
Cut in 2-inch strips and let harden.
Wrap individually in wax paper and refrigerate.
If you like nuts, can also be added before putting into platter.

title: eggs 'n bologna breakfast
directions: Will need muffin pan.
Heat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin pan with nonstick spray (Pam).
Place the bologna slices in the muffin pan to form a cup.
Break 1 egg into the center of each bologna "cup".
Pour 1 teaspoon milk over each egg.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend cornstarch and sugar; combine with water in saucepan. Cook until thick, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add gelatin.
Allow to cool, but not completely cold.

title: german reuben casserole
directions: Combine sauerkraut, sausage, dressing and parsley in a 10 x 6-inch glass dish. Cover and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes. Sprinkle cheese and pepper over top and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, butter, baking powder and milk.
(Result is
a thin cake batter.) Pour into large greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
While cake is hot, spread peanut butter over cake. Allow to harden in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate and spread on top.
Allow to harden in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch dish with crushed Doritos.
In a separate bowl, mix chicken, mushroom soup, chicken soup, broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Pour over Doritos.
Top with the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey meatballs(diet)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in a medium-size bowl and mix well.
Shape into balls and place on a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake 35 minutes until browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Combine butter, Romano, flour and chicken base in medium saucepan.
After butter melts add half and half cream and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When alfredo starts to boil add sherry.
Serve over fettucine.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture slowly until all mixed.
Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until center is done. Cool and cut.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Heat milk and soften bread in it.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in well-greased pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Let stand in pan 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot spiced fruit cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until the sugar is dissolved. Warm over the stove top (do not boil).
Serve warm.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add apple juice and pineapple juice.
Serve hot.
Do not overheat fruit juice.
Yields 25 servings.

title: chocolate kahlua cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, chopped nuts and butter in medium bowl.
Blend with pastry blender until crumbly.
Press on bottom and sides of 2 buttered and floured 9-inch pie plates.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Blend well.
Sprinkle thoroughly with humor.
Season with consideration, respect and pride.
Spread over a lifetime and serve generously.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt chocolate and butter in medium saucepan.
Gradually blend in sugar and flour, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in egg yolks, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: zucchini nut bread or muffins
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Then mix together rest of ingredients and add to first mixture.
For bread, grease and flour two 8 x 5-inch loaf pans, bake at 350° for 1 hour and remove from pan immediately.
For muffins, grease or line two muffin pans (12 cup) with baking paper cups.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes about 2 or 2 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: biscuit christmas tree
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Separate biscuits from two cans of biscuits.
At center top of ungreased baking sheet, place a biscuit, then make two rows of 2 below, then two rows of 3 and two rows of 4 biscuits, making "tree" shape as you go along.
Final biscuit is made into oval and placed at center bottom of base. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Frost while hot with light green powdered sugar glaze.
Put large whole maraschino or candied cherries in hollows where biscuits come together and cherry halve on edges and at peak of tree.
Sprinkle with green colored sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese crackers.

title: olive's casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat and add vegetables and seasonings, also tomato sauce.
Blend cheeses together.
Spoon 1/2 of cooked noodles into greased casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Pour meat sauce over all.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Spread chopped pecans on top; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Butter a baking dish or skillet.
Arrange a layer of apples in dish; sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add rest of apples.
Top with crumbs made by working together butter, 1 cup brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo; set aside.
Mix vegetables, rice, soup and cheese.
Add onion mixture and 1/2 can water.
Put in casserole. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Stir halfway through baking time.

title: yellow cake
directions: Measure into mixing bowl the flour, sugar, Crisco, salt and 2/3 cup milk.
Blend by hand or with mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Now stir in baking powder.
Now add eggs, 1/3 cup milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend by hand or in mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes until the batter is smooth and thin.
Pour into pans which have been rubbed with Crisco and lined with heavy paper. Bake in two 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
When cool, frost with chocolate or white icing.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken 10 minutes in lime juice, oil, chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute chicken, onion and green pepper until chicken is done.
Heat tortillas according to package directions.
Fill tortilla with chicken mixture, cheese, salsa and sour cream; fold or roll (the meat mixture can be wrapped in foil to cook on the grill over medium hot coals).

title: "sweet earth" dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Mix together pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Crush Oreos.
Using a 12 to 14-inch high flower pot (plastic), layer Oreo and mixture.
Begin and end with Oreos. Place plastic flower in middle of pot and fool people with edible dirt.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients except half the butter and the cornflakes.
Place into a 9x13-inch baking dish and pat down.
Sprinkle with the crushed cornflakes over the potatoes.
Pour the remaining butter over the cornflakes.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour.
Yield: 8-10 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Skin, debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add water; mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll on floured board thin as possible.
Cut in strips.
Drop in boiling chicken broth; simmer for about 20 minutes, or until dumplings are tender.
Add chicken; set aside until ready to serve.

title: venison roast
directions: Soak game
in
water
and
baking soda overnight in the refrigerator to remove the "gamey" taste.
Salt and pepper the roast and set
aside.
Fry	the
bacon
in	a Dutch oven large enough to
accommodate
your roast.
Remove bacon to drain and set aside,
reserving drippings.
Flour the roast and brown on all sides
in
the
large roasting pan.
Surround with onions, potatoes, carrots,	apples	and cooked bacon.
Add one inch of water.
Add herbs.	Cover and
cook at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.* Thicken pan juices with a little flour if desired.

title: salsa dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Mix hamburger meat with salsa and picante sauce. Cook a little.
Pour hamburger mixture over cream cheese. Spread cheese over hamburger mixture and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve over crushed Tostitos chips or use for a dip with the chips.

title: stuffed banana pepper
directions: Cut open banana peppers long way.
Dice jalapeno peppers real small; mix with cheese.
Stuff banana peppers with cheese and jalapeno peppers.
Melt cheese in oven.

title: chocolate chiffon icebox pie
directions: Pour cold water in bowl and add gelatine; soak.
Mix cocoa and boiling water.
Add to gelatine and stir well.
Add the slightly beaten egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat the egg whites until start getting stiff, then gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, continuing to beat until stiff peaks are formed.
When egg yolk mixture starts to thicken, add to egg white mixture.
Fill baked pie shell and chill.
Just before serving, spread with a not too thick coating of whipped cream.
This is for a 9-inch pie.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Place in bowl; add green pepper, celery and onion.
Mix oil and vinegar with sugar, salt and black pepper. Pour over bean mixture and toss.
Refrigerate (covered).
Serves 10.

title: microwave creamy chicken
directions: Blend soup, mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce.
Place chicken breasts into casserole dish and pour mixture over them.
Place plastic wrap over dish and cook in microwave for 10 minutes.
Turn and cook 10 minutes more or until done.
Blend in sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Combine ingredients. Beat well. Bake at 350° until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cholesterol free deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half.
Remove yolks and throw away.
Peel baked potato and mash with fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Butter side of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugars, cream, milk and butter.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugars are dissolved and mixture comes to a boiling point, then cook to a soft ball stage (238°) or tested in cold water, stirring only if necessary.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm without stirring.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat until very thick. Pour into buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ingredients in layers in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, pineapple and cream cheese; let set until smooth. Add marshmallows and walnuts.
Let it cool.
Whip the cream and add to this mixture.
Let set several hours until ready to serve.

title: impossible pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; set aside to cool.
Beat eggs well. Add sugar and butter and mix well.
Add flour, coconut and milk, stirring until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Crust forms while baking.

title: holiday orange eggnog
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in milk, blending well.
Gradually stir in orange juice.
Serve in small mugs or cups; sprinkle each serving with a little grated orange peel and a dash of nutmeg. Yields 24 cups.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; let partially set.
Pour milk in shallow pan and place in freezer until crystals form throughout, then pour into bowl and beat until soft peaks form.
Add lemon juice, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold jello into whipped milk; stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before eating.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Mix up 1/2 stick butter while still hot.
Add 1 can Carnation milk, eggs, milk and 1/2 cup grated mild cheese.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hot cucumber soup
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Dice them.
Put onion and cucumbers in butter in frypan.
Saute 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken broth. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Put in blender with dill, curry powder and cream.
Blend until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in saucepan and heat just to boiling point (don't continue to let boil).

title: white enchiladas
directions: Mix together all ingredients except corn chips and cheese.
In 3-quart casserole, layer corn chips, soup mixture and cheese in that order.
Make two layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peel-a-pound soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pan (Dutch oven) and cover with water.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender. Garnish with Parmesan cheese, if you like.

title: sandies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat butter until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add water and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in flour and nuts.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix all and chill.
Thirty minutes before serving, mix 1 small carton of sour cream with 1 package of cream cheese.
Stir into salad and chill until serving time.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fresh fruit.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Toast bread slices; trim crust.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a small skillet over low heat.
Add cinnamon, confectioners sugar and if desired, a grating of nutmeg.
Cook for about a minute after it bubbles, stirring constantly.
Spread on one side of the toast and run under the broiler for about 30 seconds, until a glossy crust forms.
Watch that toast doesn't burn.

title: open-face crab muffins
directions: Mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Split muffins and toast.
Spread with mayonnaise mixture.
Mix the rest of the mayonnaise mix, crab and Worcestershire sauce; spread over muffins.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Broil about 3 inches from heat until cheese is melted.

title: taco chips ole
directions: Brown the turkey and onion together in a large skillet.
Add the next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put the remaining ingredients in bowls.

title: aunt georgie's stew
directions: Put soup and 1 can water in a rectangular cake pan.
Peel potatoes and carrots; cut into large chunks.
Cut onion into 4 sections.
Cut meat into strips; combine everything in a cake pan and sprinkle basil leaves on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: egg-cheese casserole
directions: Microwave the white sugar and white corn syrup on High for 4 minutes.

Using a wooden spoon, stir in peanuts and microwave 3 1/2 minutes. Add butter and vanilla. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Stir. Add baking soda and mix well. Pour into prepared baking sheet and spread to desired thickness. Let cool completely. Lightly bang baking sheet on countertop to break up the candy.

title: 7-up sherbet punch
directions: Put the 2 quarts of sherbet in a large punch bowl; let stand at room temperature.
Just before serving when sherbet is soft, add the 7-Up and stir several times.
Makes 50 generous servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar.
Add eggs, marmalade and cooked potato.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with orange juice.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake covered for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Uncover and bake 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Make sure
chicken
is cooked completely.
Mix chicken, celery, onion, almonds
and
salt. Add lemon juice and mustard to mayonnaise.
Fold
in chicken mixture.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole
dish.
Sprinkle with chips and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked flounder
directions: Place fillet on greased pan.
Combine cheese and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Boil vegetables and potatoes 10 to 12 minutes or until done. While they are cooking, melt margarine in large Dutch oven.
Add onion, salt, pepper and flour to melted margarine; mix until smooth.
Add milk and cheese, stirring, until cheese is melted. Pour vegetables with their water into cheese sauce.
Stir 3 to 5 minutes until smooth and thick.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water until tender; drain.
Beat until light.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/3 of cheese and bread crumbs for the top layer.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and is light brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut breasts in half; pound to thin.
Put ham and Swiss cheese on and cover with other half chicken breast; pin with toothpicks. Roll in flour, then egg and milk, then cracker crumbs.
Place butter and parsley in baking dish.
Roll breaded chicken in melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes more.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend at room temperature.
Form into small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: jew bread
directions: Melt margarine; let cool.
Mix other ingredients with margarine.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican meat dip
directions: Fry meat and drain off grease.
Put in pan.
Fry sausage and mash up in little pieces.
Drain off grease and use some of it to saute chopped onion.
Put all in pan.
Add soup, tomatoes and chilies and mix.
Cut up cheese in small pieces; cook all together.
Keep hot in crock-pot or chafing dish.

title: frozen punch
directions: In a saucepan, cook sugar and water for about 8 to 10 minutes to syrupy stage, then cool.
Mix cooled syrup with all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Pour into molds and freeze.
(It takes at least one or two days to freeze completely.)
When ready to use, remove molds from freezer and place in punch bowl.
Pour chilled ginger ale over frozen punch.
Allow about a half hour at least for mold to start to melt and mix with ginger ale.
When it looks like slush, it's at its best!

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef; drain. Add green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, corn and seasonings; add 1/2 can onions.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until heated through.
Spoon beef mixture into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half; arrange so cut edges face side of dish and ends overlap.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Top with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a casserole dish, mixing well. After mixed, cover the top with the Ritz crackers.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes, so crackers can brown.

title: colossal cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat together butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in oats, chocolate and baking soda.
Mix well.
Drop by scant 1/4 cup dry measurement about 4 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: the meal stretcher
directions: If
hamburger
is being used, brown, then drain the fat from it.
If
Spam is being used, chop it into chunks.
Bring to boil 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Add can
of drained
corn
and Spam or cooked hamburger.
Cook on medium heat.
After
stirring well, let it stay for 1 minute. Serve as is, or over rice.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook and season; drain.
Mix last 6 ingredients well.
Alternate sauce with layer of vegetables.
End with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° until sauce bubbles.
Cover with cracker crumbs and brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Beat egg; add milk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add seasonings.
Drop by spoonful in hot deep fat (375°) and cook until brown.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli rice dish
directions: Let the bean mixture set unrefrigerated for at least 24 hours. Beans must be at room temperature before preparing the corn bread as follows.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and add the sugar gradually, but don't overwork it or let it become oily.
Gradually work in flour and cornstarch.

title: black magic cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Stir sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 40 minutes; cool.
Frost as desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pig eaters cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in 8-inch pan, 20 to 25 minutes in long pan.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Pour the pie filling into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Combine the other ingredients.
Spread this over the top of the blueberries.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until the topping is browned.
Serve warm, alone or with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: canadian cheese soup(microwave)
directions: Combine water, potato, onion, carrot and celery in 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at High until potatoes are tender, 12 to 17 minutes.
Stir once.
Stir in consomme and half and half. Cover.
Microwave at Medium-high for 6 to 8 minutes.
Mix in cheese, stirring until melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pesto chicken and pasta
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and set aside. Place oil in a hot wok, tilting to coat surface. Add chicken, stirring well. Cook about 4 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Stir in sliced mushrooms and tomato wedges. Cook for 4 to 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Combine chicken broth and cornstarch. Stir until smooth. Add to chicken mixture and cook for 5 to 6 minutes or until slightly thickened. Add 1 tablespoon pesto sauce, stirring well. Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Combine hot fettuccine and remaining pesto sauce, tossing gently. Serve chicken mixture over pasta. Garnish with basil sprig, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: curry of lamb
directions: Brown meat in hot fat over medium heat; add onion and cook until yellow.
Add curry mixed with flour; allow to bubble.
Add bouillon cubes dissolved in water, catsup, salt, apples and celery; simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with hot fluffy rice.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place cheese in bowl.
Add package of beef, Worcestershire sauce and green onions.
Take hands and mix; form a ball.
Place the other package of beef on wax paper.
Spread evenly and roll ball over it until covered.

title: rich butter sauce
directions: Brown flour in butter over medium heat.
Add water gradually, stirring constantly to form a smooth sauce.
Season and continue stirring until sauce thickens.
The sauce may be enriched by adding well blended egg yolks.

title: maraschino nut cake
directions: Sift 3 times first four items.
Add shortening, cherry juice, cherries and milk.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Fold in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Coat pan with shortening and flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend together and bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Good frosted with your favorite cream cheese frosting.

title: the reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a layer on bottom of long baking dish. Cover sauerkraut with uncooked egg noodles.
Mix soup, mustard, onion and milk.
Pour over noodles.
Crumble corned beef over this layer.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over corned beef, and top with rye bread crumbs coated with melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a saucepan, mix the sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch and nutmeg. Add the salt and water.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Add the lemon juice.
Pour over sliced apples in jars.
Leave 1-inch headspace.
Cold pack in boiling water bath 20 minutes.

title: lainie's dip
directions: Put in blender and mix well.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, butter and sugars.
Press into buttered pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Do not bake too long. Melt chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter and nuts.
Pour over bars. Spread frosting while still hot.

title: easy crab bisque
directions: Combine soups, milk, cream and seafood seasoning.
Add crabmeat gently; do not break up too much.
Heat to just below boiling.
Add sherry just before serving.
Garnish with chives.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Make roux with butter and flour; add chicken stock and milk. Cook until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cubed potato.
Serve garnished with cheese, bacon and chives.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Cut in half (lengthwise).
Scoop out potatoes and whip with remaining ingredients.
Refill shells and reheat at 425° for 15 minutes. They will freeze nicely.

title: cocktail dessert
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add egg and vanilla.
Fold in fruit cocktail and juice.
Put in a buttered 8 x 12-inch or 7 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peppers stuffed with rice
directions: Mix desired ingredients and fill tomatoes.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in baking dish at 350°.

title: quick breads
directions: Sift white flour; measure and sift with salt and baking powder. Add graham or whole wheat flour. Combine sugar, water, molasses and milk. Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins. Mix thoroughly. Pour into well oiled baking pans.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour. Makes 2 small loaves.

title: mustard glazed corned beef
directions: Place brisket in a large ovenproof Dutch oven.
Add water and next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until brisket is tender.
Drain and discard cloves, garlic, bay leaves and rosemary.
Return brisket to Dutch oven or place in a baking pan.
Combine mustard, orange marmalade, horseradish, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and sugar in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Spoon 1/2 cup mustard mixture over beef brisket.
Set remaining mustard mixture aside.
Bake brisket, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer brisket to a serving platter.
If desired, garnish with orange slices and rosemary sprigs.
Serve with remaining mustard mixture.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chipman's chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat egg; add oil and beat again.
Add the rest of ingredients and stir.
Brush sauce on the chicken every few minutes during cooking.

title: pork chops with wild rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and 1 1/4 c. water in a 2 qt. casserole dish. Add chinese vegetables.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with pepper to taste. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chinese noodles and soy sauce.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Make your crust first.
Mix together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan frosting
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, margarine, eggs and dash of salt in saucepan.
Cook on low heat until thickens.
Add vanilla. Stir in, then add coconut and pecans.
Let cool.

title: our favorite mexican lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef; add green peppers and microwave 6 minutes. Stir twice.
After meat loses pink color; drain.
Add onion soup mix, chili powder, tomato sauce and paste, olives and water. Microwave 5 minutes, until heated.
Place 2 tortilla shells in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish (microwavable).
Top with 1/2 meat mixture, then 1/2 of both cheeses; repeat.
Microwave for 5 minutes.
Rotate dish.
Microwave 5 more minutes, until cheese has melted.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve hot.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes.
In large skillet, combine meat, green pepper, onion and salt; cook and stir over medium heat until meat browns.
Pour off fat.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in eggs and tomato sauce.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven, arrange onions and, if desired, additional cheese slices on top.
Bake 2 minutes longer.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tofu tuna bake(vegetarian)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil 2 quart baking dish.
Combine tuna, mayonnaise, onion, peppers, lemon juice, cheese, and peas in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Cut tofu in small cubes; stir into mixture.
Spoon into baking dish; sprinkle with almonds and wheat germ.
Bake about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Prepare oven to 375°.
Mash potatoes until well blended.
Add butter, sugar and eggs, stirring well after each addition.
Add lemon juice, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend until of smooth consistency. Add milk, stirring so mixture will not become lumpy. Sprinkle flour over butter.
Stir into mixture.
Pour into pie shells. Bake 30 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.

title: kitchen volcano
directions: Place an 8 to 10 ounce cup or glass on a pie plate or other tray.
Pour vinegar into cup.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Pour in baking soda and stand back.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and meat in hot fat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours adding water if necessary.
Add beans; heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: very rocky road fudge(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass measure, cook sugar, 1 cup marshmallows, milk and margarine on High for 4 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes, until melted, stirring once during cooking.
Stir; cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in nuts and remaining marshmallows.
Spread in foil-lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 24 pieces.
Preparation time:
4 minutes.
Cooking time:
6 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wash chicken.
Boil chicken breasts for about 1 hour.
Fix stuffing according to directions on box.
Heat soup (use milk instead of water to thin).
Take chicken off of bone.
Then layer casserole dish:
stuffing and chicken; pour soup on top.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles.

title: **confetti cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage, cover with ice water; lift cabbage from water. Place in saucepan with other ingredients.
Cover, turn to high heat until steaming.
Reduce to low; cook 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix well, make into patties or balls.
Brown in skillet using a small amount of oil.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine sugar and margarine.
Add egg yolks one at a time. Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Beat egg whites and add.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: aunt abby's raisin filled cookies
directions: Make a dough to handle easy and roll. Cut in cookies. Bake on top rack at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: herbed-mustard chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts 2 minutes on each side in a skillet sprayed with Pam.
Add seasonings and juice.
Stir.
Simmer 7 to 10 minutes, until meat is cooked through and sauce is thick enough to coat meat.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Combine powdered sugar and Marshmallow Creme in a plastic bag and knead to mix.
Divide dough into rolls of 1/4 cup each and freeze for 20 minutes.
Dip into melted caramel and roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown turkey, onion and garlic; drain. Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Stir until blended.
Grease 2 round casseroles.
Layer tortilla sauce and cheese (start and end with tortillas).
Pour water over all and bake, uncovered.
Add remaining cheese.
Cover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool in refrigerator for 48 hours. Peel and grate (hand grater works best) in big casserole dish. Add the grated cheese and chopped onion.
Mix the warmed half and half, melted butter and salt and pour over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water, sugar, pineapple and salt.
Then whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip.
Add gelatin mixture.
In large round bowl, make alternate layers of gelatin mix and cake pieces starting with gelatin mix. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and top with 1 envelope of Dream Whip.

title: eagle brand cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle brand until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon brand and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: cheeseburger or hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring until it crumbles; drain.
Return beef to skillet.
Stir in salt and next 3 ingredients; cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce; reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon into an 8-inch square baking dish; top with cheese, if desired.
Flatten biscuits into 3 1/2 inch circles, and place on top of casserole, directly over cheese slices, if used.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are browned.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: meringue shells
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute, then on high for 15 minutes.
Cut brown paper to fit 2 cookie pans.
Grease paper lightly.
Drop meringue by tablespoon onto paper, placing 4 meringues on each cookie sheet.
Indent top of meringue with large spoon to form a nest shape.
Bake at 275° until browned.
Baked meringue shells can be filled with strawberries and topped with whipped cream.

title: grandma's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, then flour. Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes, but watch carefully.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; melt margarine and add to dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and add, one at a time.
Next, add vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
The middle will shake, but pie will be done.
Do not overbake!

title: sausage pie
directions: Spray a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Line bottom of dish with half of the crescent rolls.
Smooth them flat.
In bowl, mix sausage and eggs together and pour over rolls.
Slice cheese and place over mixture.
Layer the remaining rolls over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Best to let set a minutes before serving.
(You can experiment with the different mixtures to go in the pie.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken until tender; cool, debone and save broth. Saute peppers and onions in margarine until tender.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth until broth is absorbed.
Mix together onions, peppers, peas, Ro-Tel, pimento and chopped chicken.
Add 2 cups cubed Velveeta cheese and all other ingredients; heat slowly until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream, beating after each addition.
Add extracts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: slow boat to china
directions: Brown beef.
Add celery, onions and saute a few minutes. Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: fudge upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add the milk, then add the sifted ingredients. Mix well and add the chopped nuts. Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine the remaining cup of sugar, brown sugar and 2/3 cup cocoa. Spread this evenly over the mixture in the pan and slowly pour the boiling water over all. Bake 40 minutes. Remove from the oven and place on cake rack. Serve warm with whipped topping or when cool. In dishing up this dessert, be sure to cut down to bottom of the pan, because the rich, fudge-like topping is there. Serve upside down or in squares with the whipped topping. Serves 8.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown onions and hamburger together; season to taste.
Pour off excess fat and add 1/2 can green chilies (keep other half for sauce).
Make sauce and pour a thin layer on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll meat in tortillas, 2 or 3 tablespoons to each one.
Place in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over top of tortillas and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: pumpkin pie(grandma's)
directions: Use Mom's pie crust recipe or pastry shells.

title: american chop suey
directions: Can be creative and individualized by adding celery, eggplant, zucchini, etc. to saute and by adding favorite spices.

title: rice chile verde
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer half the rice, half the sour cream mixed with the onions and chilies, half the grated cheese, all the tomato slices and repeat the rice, sour cream, cheese, layering once more. Sprinkle with parsley or paprika for color after heating and before serving.
Heat in microwave of a 350° oven.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs. Beat whites well and add 1/3 cup sugar. Beat yolks; add juice, water, sugar and butter. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick (like pancake batter). Beat in 1/3 of egg whites with spoon. Pour into baked pie shell and cover with remainder of egg whites. Place in 425° oven and bake until lightly brown on top.

title: dressing
directions: Add chopped giblets, 3/4 to 1 cup broth.
Pour over all and mix well.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes with chicken or turkey.

title: lemon-coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add butter flavoring and lemon extract.
Mix well. Add flour slowly, using barely 2 cups.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that has been well-greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: quick casserole
directions: Brown beef in large saucepan; drain.
Add other ingredients; heat and stir until heated through (5 minutes).
Serve.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, mix the two soups, Ro-Tel (cut up) and onion.
In pan, first layer is 1/3 of corn tortillas, then 1/3 of chicken, 1/3 of sauce and 1/3 cheese. Continue layering until all ingredients are used, finishing with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion.
Blend in sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Put in greased pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
In small bowl, mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour. Pour over meat mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Can add peppers, mushrooms, Italian sausage or bacon, if desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oleo.
Sift together cinnamon, allspice and flour.
Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Combine all by rotating flour mixture and applesauce to sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly and add 1 or 2 cups of raisins and nuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wine dates stuffed
directions: Cover dates with
wine	for
about 1 hour.
Drain dates and insert a nut meat or a candied cherry.
Roll in granulated sugar.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together and chill and serve.

title: nanna's shortcake and strawberry dip
directions: Blend flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Mix in milk and pat into round cake pan.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned and pick is clean.

title: "ono"licious cornbread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add Bisquick, cornmeal and milk.
Mix very well.
Grease and flour pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° (preheated oven) for approximately 35 minutes, or until golden color on top.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package and let cool.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Spread cooled pudding, morsels and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer squash, onion, tomatoes and seasoning each layer.
Top with layer of grated mild Cheddar cheese and bacon strips.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll in 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.
(These are better if they are covered tight for a day or two and refrigerated.)

title: cuban cube steak
directions: In skillet, heat a little oil on high.
Add cube steak and reduce heat slightly.
Pan-fry steak until just done; then salt and pepper.
Remove to a heated platter and squeeze lime over each steak.
Then top with green onions and parsley.

title: vinegar rolls
directions: Combine vinegar, 1 cup sugar, water and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Stir until well dissolved and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Set aside.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix in a double boiler, then place over boiling water.
Beat with an electric mixer constantly until frosting stands in peaks. Remove from heat and frost cake.
This frosting is great on a fresh coconut cake.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dice apples and celery into small pieces, chop walnuts coarsely.
Combine with mayonnaise and salt.
Mix well and place in refrigerator to chill.
Serve mounded on lettuce leaves, top with maraschino cherry, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp for 2 to 3 minutes; drain shrimp.
Combine oil, vinegar, capers, celery seed, salt and Tabasco.
Place shrimp in shallow dish.
Cover with bay leaves and slices of onions.
