Pour oil and vinegar mixture over shrimp.
The shrimp should be chilled for at least 24 hours and can be stored in refrigerator for up to a week.
To serve, drain shrimp and use toothpicks.

title: easy pie crust(my sister, luella, makes the best pie crust.)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Divide dough in half, and place ball between two pieces of waxed paper.
With rolling pin, roll out dough and place on pie plate.
Do second dough the same way.

title: tuna cheese puff
directions: Combine milk, oleo, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, then add flour all at once and mix well. Stir in eggs, one at a time, making sure to blend well after each addition.
Drain tuna of excess oil and flake it.
Stir in tuna, 1/4 cup Swiss cheese and cream to mixture.
Spread batter into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Brush the top with the beaten egg and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until puffed and brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Bake in a tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
No need to ice.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Fill with vanilla pudding mixed with skim milk (beat until thickened).
Fold in coconut.
Top with Dream Whip. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a long Pyrex dish and refrigerate.
This can be made several days ahead.

title: julie's cake mix chocolate  chip cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, egg, milk, and soft butter.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie pan.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Melt oleo.
Mix all ingredients and place by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Put rest of the dough in airtight container and store in refrigerator.
Will last 3 or 4 days.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes; combine in a large bowl with butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cook cocoa, butter and milk until boils, 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop on cookie sheet layered with wax paper.
Put in fridge.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add shrimp to vegetables.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix soups, water and seasonings.
Mix vegetables, shrimp and crab with soup base and other ingredients.
Pour over rice bed.
Cook covered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except candy in large mixer bowl.
Mix on lowest speed until dough sticks together.
Shape dough into balls, using rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar; place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy kiss; press down firmly so cookie cracks around edges.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken in 3 cups water.
Drain, reserving broth. Remove from bone, skin and dice.
Break toasted bread into small pieces.
Combine bread, chicken, eggs, butter, celery and onion; mix well.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour broth over top.
Salt and pepper.
Spread mushroom soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion, Old Bay, salt and pepper to taste.
Fold in crab meat.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered bread cubes and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: pistachio-pineapple delight
directions: Combine Jell-O, pineapple (do not drain), marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine casserole ingredients and pour into a shallow, buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Mix topping ingredients together and spread over casserole.

title: curry dip briton
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: layered salad
directions: Wash and tear spinach.
Place in bottom of a clear, glass bowl.
Wash and tear lettuce for next layer.
Chop onion and place on top of lettuce.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise
together. Carefully spread over mixture.
Seal edges.
Just before serving, top with remaining ingredients. May be sprinkled with salt and pepper.

title: new years and other party time dip
directions: Add peppers, onion and garlic to drained peas.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Transfer mixture to blender or food processor.
Puree. Add melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Top with chiles and liquid.
Add cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts, about 12 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Serve with chips.

title: christmas gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to jello mixture. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream of asparagus(quick soup)
directions: Place broth, asparagus and onion in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Ladle into blender or food processor; blend at medium speed until well mixed. Return to saucepan.
Whisk mildly; season with salt and pepper. Heat soup thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut unpared zucchini into 1/2-inch slices. Cook, covered, in 1-inch of boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Beat eggs. Stir in all ingredients with eggs except cheeses and meat.
Place in the bottom of pan half of the zucchini.
Add half of the egg and rice mixture.
Lightly sprinkle 1/3 to 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layer of zucchini, then rice mix. Add Parmesan cheese on top, then add meat on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
After the first 30 minutes of baking, add shredded Longhorn cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into balls or logs. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown bee in skillet. Add onion and garlic; saute until tender. Add tomatoes, mushrooms and seasonings. Simmer 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Cover and simmer another 10 - 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: candied yams
directions: Slice yams into rounds and arrange in glass dish. Sprinkle flour over yams; dot with margarine. Combine white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water; pour over yams. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until syrup is thick.

title: baked ham sandwich
directions: Split rolls, butter and brown in oven.
Makes 2 slices of ham bun size, 2 slices of onion bun size and 1 slice of tomato bun size.
Arrange in following order:
Start with bun bottom, then ham, onion, tomato, Blue cheese, ham, onion and bun top.
Salt and pepper sandwich to taste as you build sandwich.

title: hot russian tea
directions: Mix all together and put in jar.
For 1 cup, put 1 teaspoon mixture into cup and add hot water.

title: denise's pot pie
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Boil chicken for 15 or 20 minutes (chop in fine pieces or shred).
In a bowl, mix all ingredients together except pie crust.
Grease 1 1/2 to 2 quart dish with Pam.
Take 1 pie crust and fit into dish to make bottom crust.

Dump mixture into pie crust and cover with second pie crust and flute edges of top crust to seal the mixture inside. Pierce top with fork or cut decorative holes and bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad (casserole)
directions: Combine all ingredients (except dressing) together.
(Be sure to stir together in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.) Mix small package dressing mix with melted oleo and spread over top of salad.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, water and rice together.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Lay chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Sprinkle salt and pepper and French onion soup mix on top.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Stir ingredients, except 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese to top of dish. Put back in oven 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a 2 1/2 quart saucepan, stirring well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir well before serving.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter candy(brown stuff)
directions: Put into saucepan, butter, milk and brown sugar; cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and melt.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut.
Nuts are optional.

title: crispy croutons(microwave)
directions: In small glass bowl, heat butter 1 minute or until melted. Brush butter onto one side of bread.
Cut bread into small cubes. In an oblong glass baking dish, arrange bread and drizzle with remaining butter.
If desired, sprinkle with garlic salt or your favorite seasoning.
Heat 5 to 6 minutes or until bread is crispy, stirring twice.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Store covered.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, jello, flour, eggs and water.
Beat at medium speed for about two minutes.
Add 1/2 of the strawberries and beat for one more minute.
Add oil and beat one more minute. Divide batter evenly into two greased, floured pans and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Drain and stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic, refrigerate overnight.

title: chinese beets
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan, including the beets. Cook for
minutes
over
medium
heat or until the mixture thickens. Let cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, simmer the broth, water, bouillon, potatoes, celery, carrots and onion.
When half done, add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook until barely tender, then add undiluted soup.
Stir with vegetables; don't stir excessively.
Add chopped chicken; simmer, but do not boil.
When hot and almost ready to serve, add Velveeta cheese.
Heat slowly, until cheese is melted. Scrape bottom of pan often so cheese won't scorch.
Do not boil.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 2 hours before using.
Roll paper thin.
Fill with desired filling and fry.
While still hot, glaze.

title: *beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer in electric skillet or bake in a 300° oven for about an hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine baking soda, salt, baking powder, sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
In small bowl, beat eggs, margarine and buttermilk. Stir in raisins.
Add to dry ingredients.
Spoon mixture into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 75 minutes.
Turn bread from pan to cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: terrel's t-bird
directions: Will also need 15 pounds of coals, smoker, hickory chips and 1 six pack beer.

title: puffy cheese muffins
directions: Mix onion, black olives, mayonnaise, salt, mustard and shredded cheese thoroughly.
Spread cheese on split muffin halves. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 muffin halves.

title: baked apple-cheese pancakes
directions: Process or whisk first 6 ingredients.
Add cheese.
Cut apples into thin wedges.
Melt margarine and cook apples 2 to 3 minutes. Add other 1 tablespoon sugar as it cooks.
Spread evenly on bottom of pizza pan.
Pour batter over.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes until brown and puffy.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar; cut in wedges.

title: quickie chicken divan
directions: Boil the chicken breasts and pick the meat off the bone. Saute the celery and onion in 1 stick of butter or margarine until they are clear.
Melt the cheese in the vegetable mix and add the soup.
Cook the frozen broccoli until tender.
Mix the ingredients together in a large casserole and top with grated cheese and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: six in one cookies
directions: Cream butter gradually.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to cream mixture, beating well after each addition.
Divide dough into 6 parts.

title: bakery frosting
directions: Place all in bowl and beat with electric beater about 5 minutes or until light.
Yields enough for a layer cake.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash dish
directions: Mix good and pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and bake until firm.
Yum-Yum!

title: fruit sherbet punch
directions: Mix pineapple, orange and cherry juices together; chill. Combine ginger ale and sherbet with mixture when ready to serve.

title: georgia's divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt together.
Cook over medium heat to hard ball stage using candy thermometer.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg whites which have been stiffly beaten.
Beat with an electric mixer until candy starts to hold its shape.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Cake coloring can be used to give it color.
Pecans can be used for decoration.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package and drain. Stir in butter immediately.
Beat egg with 1 teaspoon salt, mustard and cream.
Toss macaroni with grated cheese, leaving 1/3 cup of cheese.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour on cream mixture and top with rest of cheese.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Great for a crowd of people!

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour; set excess flour aside.
In large skillet or slow-cooking pot with browning unit, heat oil.
Brown meat on all sides.
In slow-cooking pot, combine browned beef, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion, bouillon, pepper, salt, sugar and vegetables.
Pour water over all.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Turn control on high.
Thicken sauce with flour left over from coating (about 1/4 cup), dissolved in a small amount of water.
Add okra, if desired.
Cover and cook on high 10 to 15 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Makes up to 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretzel casserole
directions: Melt butter, add 1/2 cup sugar; mix well.
Add pretzels to butter/sugar mixture; mix well.
Press in bottom of baking dish and bake at 300° for 8 minutes.
Cool well.

title: three-day cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in 2 gallons of lime water for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Soak for 24 hours in 1 gallon alum water.
Drain and wash twice in water.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers; let stand 3 hours.
Place over low heat for 1 hour; do not boil.
Pack in jars, cover with vinegar liquid and seal.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; beat with mixer.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture; beat with mixer.
Stir in diced zucchini. Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes (or until toothpick comes out clean and dry).

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: raven's raspberry cake
directions: Add all ingredients together; beat on medium speed.
Pour in greased and lightly floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Great served plain or with cream cheese frosting.

title: dessert cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a ball.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: bread pot fondue
directions: Drain and chop chilies.
Slice off top of bread.
Hollow out center, leaving a 1/2-inch shell.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon filling into hollowed loaf and replace top.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux of the flour and oil by browning, being careful not to get it too hot. Add the onion, bell pepper, parsley, celery, garlic and tomatoes. Add the water to this. Cook for 30 minutes or until vegetables are transparent. Add the crab meat and a few claws for flavor, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste and a little hot sauce or Tabasco.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add parsley, garlic and shrimp. Stir in half and half, cheese and flour.
Lower flame and cook 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Boil noodles and add to mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese (optional).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or transfer to crock-pot for parties or potlucks.
Makes a lot.
(Crawfish or chicken can be substituted.)

title: greek stew
directions: Cook onions in butter until cooked, but still crisp.
Remove from pan.
Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add onions just before eating.
Heat through.

title: winter swirl
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and whip until smooth. Serves 4.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove stems and seeds from peppers.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix beef, rice, salt, pepper and onion. Add 2/3 can tomato soup.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Stand upright in small baking dish.
Pour remaining soup, diluted with 1/3 soup can of water, over peppers.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer at 350°.

title: sweet french dressing(midwest style)
directions: Shake well in jar.
Great on California green salad.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup salsa. Spread 1/4 cup salsa in a 10-inch pie plate.
Top with 3 tostadas. Top with 1/2 of each of the beans, meat mixture, sour cream and cheese.
Repeat layers; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce, remaining salsa and additional sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill overnight. Yields 10 to 12 servings.
Great with toasted fresh bread.

title: cauliflower morranco
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter with juice of 1 lemon. Saute cauliflower in butter with garlic, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and onions.
Remove stems from mushrooms; chop fine
and
add
to	meat mixture.
Cook until brown.
Add water, parsley,
salt and pepper;	bring to a boil.
Add rice, cover and remove
from
heat.
Let
stand for 5 minutes.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese,
stir
1/2 cup mayonnaise mixture into rice mixture. Spoon
into
mushrooms, place in shallow baking dish.
Top	each mushroom
with remaining mayonnaise mixture. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until brown and puffy.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until dissolved.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Pour asparagus tips into a 1-quart baking dish.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Top with fried onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Season chicken with curry powder, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil until golden.
Combine orange juice, water, brown sugar, dry mustard and mix well.
Add to chicken; simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Lift chicken from broth and add rice.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and let stand covered until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool slightly before cutting into squares.

title: frosting
directions: Cook the cornstarch and milk until thick, stirring constantly. Cool.
Beat the butter until creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
The mixture will be grainy until you add the cornstarch mixture.
Add the cornstarch mixture; beat until smooth and fluffy.

title: sweet and sour lentils
directions: Bring broth to boil in kettle.
Add bay leaf, salt and lentils or peas.
Cover; simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to mix well.
Cook for 5 minutes, or until lentils or peas are tender.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Gently press, if puffy.
Let cool.
Stir together and then spread on crust the cream cheese, salad dressing, sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll dough in rectangle.
Spread mixture on dough.
Put cheese over mixture, then pepperoni.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water, lemonade and pineapple together in gallon jug.
Freeze it.
When ready to use, mix with the ginger ale.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower in small pieces.
Use broccoli tips.
Chop onion and celery.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sour cream; sprinkle with bacon and green onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake potatoes at 300° for 30 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Take all ingredients and put in blender until mixed well.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Barbecue or bake until done.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Put mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bombay curry
directions: Brown onion and celery in hot fat.
Add meat, seasonings and gravy.
You may stretch gravy with canned gravy or bouillon.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve in ring of cooked rice.

title: turron na saging(banana rolls)
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over bananas.
Wrap each banana slice in lumpia wrapper, sealing edges with water.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: seafood wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed. Drain, put in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Brown onion, pepper and mushrooms in butter until soft.
Add to rice.
Mix in seafood and cover with cream sauce, sherry, herbs and pimento.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until thoroughly heated. Serves 6 to 8.

title: ginger's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese or Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan and 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Mix browned and drained ground beef or chicken with Prego sauce.

title: mexican sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm milk.
Add other ingredients and just enough milk to make a dough.
Roll out thin and cut in squares.
Let rise slightly.
Fry in deep fat.
Serve with honey.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in Crisco. Mix water and flour mixture.
Roll into "biscuits" and using dry flour make it kneadable.
Place on greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and brush with melted butter.
Allow to rise about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° to 400° until done.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder together.
Add to the creamed mixture; mix well.
Add oats, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim meat and cut into strips.
Brown and season with salt. Push meat over and add onion.
Cook and stir until tender.
Stir in broth, soy sauce, garlic and red pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cherry pie delight
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and pack into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Blend all ingredients. When mixed smooth, add 8 ounces chocolate chips (miniature works best).
Cook for 1 hour at 350° in a Bundt dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°
about 30 minutes or until done. Then top with grated cheese.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add berries and nuts.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; stir in just until moistened.
Pour into wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Let stand 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake loaf one hour or until done.

title: apricots with curried pork chops
directions: Brown chops quickly on both sides in skillet.
Put in casserole.
Saute onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Pour over chops. Cover and bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Top with apricot halves.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken with leek and mushroom sauce
directions: Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in a skillet and saut the chicken until lightly browned on both sides, about 5 minutes. Remove from the skillet and keep hot. Heat the other 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in the same skillet used for the chicken (do not wash out in between; you want that great chicken flavor in the bottom of the pan). Add the leeks and cook, stirring for 2 minutes. Add the sliced mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes more. Add brandy and cook for 2 minutes. Transfer this to a mixing bowl. Whisk chicken broth with flour and add to the same skillet. Cook, whisking until slightly thickened, about 3 minutes. Return mushroom mixture, chicken and juices to skillet. Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 4 minutes. Serves 4.

title: taco sauce
directions: Use rubber gloves to remove seeds from jalapenos.

title: antipasto genovese
directions: Cook asparagus spears and cauliflowerets.
Marinate asparagus, cauliflowerets, cucumber, olives, tomatoes and mushrooms in dressing for several hours; drain.
Arrange marinated vegetables on platter.
Arrange cheese triangles and rolled salami next to marinated vegetables.
Serve on a lettuce lined platter.
A great marinated salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spareribs and string beans
directions: In large pot, brown ribs.
Add onion, cooking for a few minutes.
Add tomato sauce; mix and let cook, covered, for about 15 to 20 minutes.
If using fresh string beans, you can add them now, cover and let cook until meat and string beans are tender, about an hour, stirring occasionally.
If using canned string beans, add 1/2 hour or so before done.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with Italian bread for dunking.

title: spanish rice ring(vegetable)
directions: Put all ingredients into container except rice.
Cover.
Blend for 20 seconds (puree).
Add to rice and mix.
Turn into well-greased 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Place mold in pan containing 1-inch warm water.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Cool 5 minutes; turn mold out.
Fill with creamed vegetables.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cracker crumbs.
Heat margarine and peanut butter over low heat until melted; stir into crumb mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Heat chocolate chips with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Dip balls into chocolate with tongs until coated. Refrigerate until firm.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: In saucepan, cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: italian sausage meal
directions: Cut sausage in bite sizes. Brown in a little oil. Add onions and peppers. Add tomatoes, then add some ketchup (guess the amount; this seems to sweeten it some). While all this is simmering, cook noodles and add to sausage mixture and heat through.

title: hot spinach
directions: Cook spinach in 1/4 cup water until done (do not salt). Add other ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: kolacky
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and salt.
Blend until light. Dissolve yeast in water and add to lukewarm milk.
Add half the flour and beat until smooth.
Add sugar and shortening, then add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Let raise until double in bulk or about 10 minutes.
Punch down in the middle and add you favorite filling.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Chop all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Mix noodles and veggies.
Add dressing to salad.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve.

title: easy spoon rolls
directions: Put yeast and 1 tbsp of the sugar in the water.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and yeast mixture to creamed mixture.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Put in an airtight bowl; keep in refrigerator (will keep 2-3 days).
To bake, preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spoon mixture into mini muffin pans, filling level.
Bake for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate crunchies
directions: Melt together peanut butter and shortening in 2 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat; add candies.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly with metal spoon and pressing candies with back of spoon to break up.
Chocolate will be almost melted and pieces of color coating will remain.
Remove from heat; add corn flakes, mixing until thoroughly coated.
Drop by rounded 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press one or two additional candies into mixture, if desired.
Let stand until set, about 30 minutes.

title: betty's marvelous fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring so it will not scorch.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Add marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Pour into large greased Pyrex dish.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in casserole dish.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Set aside 2 cups of Doritos.
Crumble the remaining Doritos with your hands into a large mixing bowl. Add onion, chili, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, and 1 1/2 cups cheddar cheese to the crumbled Doritos.
Stir.
Place mixture into 9 x 13 inch oven proof casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: green pea macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and cool macaroni.
Add egg, beaten and cheese, cut up. Mix, then pat in 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Take out and cool.
Brown hamburger and add Sloppy Joe mix, chopped tomatoes and frozen peas.
Put in macaroni pie shell and top with 2 slices of cheese.
Bake at 450° until bubbly.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine and whisk mustard, sesame oil, rice vinegar, soy sauce, pepper, honey, olive oil, Dijon mustard and salt.
Set aside.
Toss spinach, oranges, onion and almonds.
Combine just before serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add boiling water to oatmeal; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the shortening with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split snack
directions: In large bowl beat milk and pudding mix with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in banana slices, marshmallows and graham snacks.
Spoon evenly into dessert dishes.
Top each with whipped topping.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Before serving, garnish with a cherry, colored sprinkles and a graham snack.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add vanilla, salt and nuts; mix well. Add sifted flour last. Shape into balls and bake in 350° oven for 14 to 17 minutes. While warm, shake in a sack of powdered sugar.

title: holiday pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and stir in sour cream last.
Place in pie plate.
Top with walnuts.
Bake in oven at 350° or in microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve on party crackers, Wheat Thins, etc.
Recipe can be frozen; extend cooking time.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute
onion and pepper in fat.
Add tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Bring to a boil; stir in rice, cover and cook over low heat about 30 minutes.

title: baked corn(an amish recipe)
directions: Melt butter and add the flour.
Add milk gradually and bring to boiling point.
Stirring constantly, add corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until corn is firm.
Serves 4.

title: inside-outside ravioli
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil. Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well and save liquid. Add water to spinach liquid to equal 1 cup. Add spinach liquid and spaghetti sauce along with tomato paste; salt and pepper to ground beef mixture. Combine and simmer 10 minutes. Combine spinach, macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs, egg and oil. Spread macaroni mixture in 13 x 9 pan. Cover with sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes. Then serve.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add part of the Carnation milk and pudding mix.
Blend well.
Add remainder of Carnation milk, salt and enough milk to fill to the fill line of a 1-gallon freezer.

title: herb cream cheese dip(for fresh vegetables)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
This is a small recipe and should be doubled if you're expecting company.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra and drain.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces; coat with flour.
Salt okra before cooking.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold in okra.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Grease casserole dish lightly.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
For parties, double recipe.
Serve with crackers.

title: mounds candy
directions: Put syrup, sugar and water together. Bring to a soft ball tested in water. Beat egg whites stiff and pour hot syrup over them.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Add coconut to syrup mixture and mix well to stick together (firmly).
Chill in refrigerator. Shape into any size mounds you desire.
Chill for a few hours and coat with chocolate candy coating.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix oil, sugar, and eggs.
Mix flour and soda and mix to first mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Put in loaf pan that has been greased or sprayed with nonstick cooking spray (Pam).
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add cracker crumbs and top with remaining ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut into bars.

title: glazed pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pudding mix and pineapple juice.
Set aside.
Arrange pineapple slices in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place walnut or cherry half in center of each. Pour pudding mixture over pineapple.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Combine cake mix, instant pudding, eggs, water and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour over pineapple mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean and cake begins to pull from sides of pan.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter and let stand 1 minute.
Then remove from pan.

title: brandy alexander
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides. Spoon evenly into glasses.
Garnish, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large container. Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: t's ham steak
directions: Place slice of ham in shallow baking pan.
Broil 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove pan; turn ham and spread uncooked side with mixture of mustard and honey.
Replace under low broiler heat for 10 minutes, watching closely so that it does not burn.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked crappie
directions: Salt and pepper fish.
Combine margarine and lemon juice.
Dip fish in butter mixture, then roll in crushed crackers.
Place on a foil-lined baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of fish.

title: easy sloppy joes(mild - not too spicy)
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, pepper, onion, margarine, eggs, salt, milk, cheese and 1 cup herb stuffing. Sprinkle top with additional 1/2 cup herb stuffing. Bake 40 minutes at 375°. Serves 10.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: Brown chicken in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add soup, water and vegetable combo.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp and sliced lemons, in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil, stirring frequently; reduce to simmer after 1 minute.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Pour a small amount of sauce in bottom of a casserole (to cover bottom), then make layers of shrimp alternating with lemon slices.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.
Stir halfway through to ensure all shrimp are cooking.
Be sure to serve with fresh French bread for sopping up this delicious hot sauce.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pyrex dish and freeze.
Take from freezer one hour before serving.
Can be refrozen.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat orange juice to boiling.
Mix well orange and apricot Jell-O.
Add buttermilk.
Chill until consistency of beaten eggs. Add Cool Whip.
Pour into container.
May sprinkle with nuts or cherries, if desired.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms; separate stems and caps.
Finely chop enough stems to make 1 cup.
Cook stuffing to package directions.
Add the cup of stems to boiling water.
When stuffing is finished, stuff caps.
Arrange mushrooms in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch buttered pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until heated through.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mix juice with pudding.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Chill.

title: mom's wheat rolls
directions: Put yeast into warm water.
Add sugar; melt margarine.
Add all ingredients together into large bowl.
Mix very well.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Make out about 36 medium rolls or 2 loaves.
Let rise again, approximately 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or less.

title: tasty turkey breast
directions: Fill breast cavity with celery or onions.
Place so that breast is covering the vegetables.
Spray with Baker's Joy.
Sprinkle heavily with paprika so that it is well covered.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake about 4 hours at 325°.

title: pork chops - scallop potatoes
directions: Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, water and dillweed in a small bowl; blend well.
Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in small amount of oil in large skillet.
Drain on paper towel.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugarless double thick chocolate shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender for about 30 seconds or until mixture froths.
Serves 2.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add to melted chocolate and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one.
Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk.
Add the buttermilk solution alternately with the flour, vanilla and the pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple streusel
directions: Toss together 6 cups brown sugar and 3/4 cup browns sugar. Mix flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar, oats, butter and cinnamon with a fork.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Microwave for 9 to 12 minutes on High in a 3-quart Tupperware casserole.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Layer 1/2 and repeat in order given in a glass bowl or individual glass bowls.
Make the day before and refrigerate.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease lightly and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Empty mix into large mixing bowl.
Blend in Wesson oil, apricot nectar, eggs and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed 4 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut cluster candy
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in a 200° oven.
Add the cocktail peanuts; stir altogether.
Put on wax paper by teaspoons.
Makes about 175.
Let set.
Pack in containers with wax paper in between layers.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Simmer tomatoes, chilies and sauce. Line casserole dish with chips.
Layer meat, sauce, beans; meat, sauce beans.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: good two minute cookies
directions: Heat butter or margarine, milk and sugar to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in oatmeal, cocoa and raisins, etc.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lemon glaze
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and blend until sugar is liquefied. Pour over bread.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook each item separately until nearly done.
Cold pack 2 hours.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Stir in whole cranberry sauce, nuts and pineapple.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl and freeze. Take out of freezer 30 minutes before serving time.

title: overnight lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, chives, oregano, and egg; mix well.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 1/2 cups sauce, top with half of lasagne noodles, half of Ricotta, top with half of the Mozzarella.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes, until bubbly.
Yields 12 servings.

title: diabetic chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine 2 cups milk with baking chocolate in top of double boiler.
Cook and stir over simmering water until chocolate has melted and mixture is smooth.
Sift together flour, cornstarch, Equal and salt.
Mix flour mixture with remaining 1/2 cup milk. Add to chocolate mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add some chocolate mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Then stir into pan and return to heat.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked shell and cool and set.
Top with topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, salt to taste. Drain and mash. Add butter, cracker crumbs, eggs, and milk. Mix well. Add cheese, reserving enough to sprinkle on top of dish. Place in baking dish and cook at 350° until done (about 20 or 25 minutes).

title: pear salad
directions: Bring 1 cup of pear juice to boil; add gelatin, cream cheese, Dream Whip, mashed pears and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: ham and vegetable salad
directions: In small saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add potatoes; simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, until fork-tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: uncle reg's roast possum
directions: 1. Possum is easy to catch. Hit em wif a rock or a stick when they're up a tree, and you have em in a sack in no
time. The yellow bellied goomers is too scared to fight
back and they plays dead long enough to grab em.
2. Boil up a peck o water or more, depending on the size
of your possum. Dunk your critter in the boiling water
an right away pull off his hair n' scrape him clean.
Don't forgit to cut off his fee, his bXXX's, his tail.
Clean out his inards.
3. Put the possum in a heafty jog o salty water and let
him cool overnite. Change his water the next day and
start boiling him 'til his skin lets a fork pop through
easy like. They're ain't no time for cookin' possum
cause some is tougher'n others.
4. When the feller is yis right, dry him off and put in a
bakin pan, with a bit of pot likker'n some seasoned
salt over his belley. 5. When he is brown and toasty, his ready for slicin and servin. We always serve them wit yams.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, celery and onion.
Mix all together and bake at 350° to 400° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: beef chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off fat. Salt and pepper meat. Cut chilies in half lengthwise; remove seeds. Arrange half of the chilies in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and top with meat mixture. Lay remaining chilies over meat. Beat eggs, milk and flour together until smooth; pour over chilies and meat mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes; cut into squares for serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: brown sugar cookies(fruit cookies)
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before baking at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup berries; simmer with water for 4 minutes.
Add sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Stir in butter.
Fill pie shell with sliced berries; pour cooked mixture over berries. Cool; serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip; chill until serving time.

title: cream corn muffins
directions: Mix together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in milk, oil and eggs, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in creamed corn.
Pour into greased muffin pan, filling cups to the brim.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until puffed.
Let cool 1 minute before turning onto plate.

title: hamburger over rice
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
In a bowl, mix soup and milk together.
Pour over meat; cook until soup is hot and thick enough for you.
Serve over rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in 2 quarts of water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Brown sausage and drain excess grease and set aside. Slice squash about 1/2-inch thick and place in large bowl.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Place milk, egg, onions and Cheddar cheese in bowl with squash.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold half squash into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Place sausage evenly over squash in casserole dish and spread Parmesan cheese evenly over squash.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes uncovered.
Dish can be made without sausage, if desired.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and sour cream; toss gently.
Arrange lettuce on serving plates; spoon fruit mixture on each.
Place banana half on each side of this.
Top with coconut and a cherry.

title: pasta dressing
directions: Mix well and pour over favorite pasta mixture.
Remainder can be kept in refrigerator for weeks, but will separate and will need to be shook up.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
well,
except milk.
Then add milk and blend all together.
May have to add a little water to get it well blended.
Press into desired container.
Wrap well and store in refrigerator.
Delicious and so easy!

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Add bacon drippings, shallots and celery in large frying pan. Saute until tender.
Add mushrooms, cooked rice and soy sauce. Cook 10 minutes on low heat stirring occasionally.
Stir in egg and cook until done.
Stir in crumbled bacon and serve.
Add extra soy sauce if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh cucumber salad
directions: Put all of the above into a quart jar and shake or stir to mix well.
Let
chill
for
hours
or overnight for best flavor.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, measure, add salt, baking powder and sift again. Cut in shortening, gradually add milk and make in soft dough. Bake about 15 or 20 minutes at 450°.

title: cold beef platter
directions: Roast rump roast at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in shallow dish.
Arrange next 2 ingredients over meat.
Blend remaining ingredients; pour over roast.
Cover and chill 2 1/2 hours.
Drain marinade.
Arrange on platter.
Serves 6.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, apples and raisins in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrot mixture, tossing to coat.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions.
Drain.
Set aside.
Slice zucchini, olives, mushrooms and red pepper.
Make dressing according to package directions.
Marinate vegetables in dressing for 2 to 4 hours.
Drain vegetables and mix with ravioli. Sprinkle shredded Parmesan cheese.
Serve cold.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and Serve.

title: working girl salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese thoroughly.
Blend in Jell-O and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Easy for a working girl to get together.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, cornstarch, allspice, egg, cream and salt.
Shape into small balls.
Drop balls into hot oil in skillet.
Brown well on all sides.
Transfer balls to warm plate. Blend flour with remaining fat in skillet.
Stir in water, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring until smooth. Arrange meatballs in sauce and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Great with mashed potatoes!

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juice.
Put in saucepan all juice and water.
Stir in pudding mix.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill overnight.
Just before serving, fold in sliced banana.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the first 3 ingredients and cool 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in moderate oven, 350°.

title: lemon zucchini muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and nutmeg.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
In small bowl, beat eggs with fork; beat in milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, then sprinkle zucchini on top.
Stir just until blended.
Fill greased muffin pan(s) 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until pick inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 25 minutes for muffins, 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch square coffee cake.
Makes 12 regular size muffins or one 9-inch cake.

title: spinach stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake the potatoes 1 hour.
Steam spinach about 4 to 5 minutes; drain and squeeze dry and drain. Split the potatoes lengthwise and scoop out the pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch thick shell.
Mash the pulp with butter and milk; add spinach, scallions, nutmeg, salt, pepper and cottage cheese. Spoon mixture into potatoes and sprinkle with Gruyere.
Bake potatoes approximately
6 minutes, until heated and lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: smothered steak
directions: Roll steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil. Pour rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with browned steak. Mix bouillon, onion, celery, wine vinegar and water in saucepan. Cook until onion and celery are tender.
Mix sour cream and soup with bouillon mixture and pour over steak.
Bake in oven at 275° for 2 hours.
By using the wine vinegar this gives the taste of stroganoff.

title: hollywood chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine and flour in a small saucepan.
Slowly add milk and bring to boil over low flame, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add sugar, salt, onion, paprika and pepper.
While making white sauce, cook one 10 ounce package frozen mixed vegetables.

title: coconut cream meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
With wire whisk, blend in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
In small bowl, beat about 1/4 cup of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Pour egg yolks into saucepan, stirring rapidly to prevent lumping.
Return to low heat; cook 3 more minutes, stirring constantly (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine and extracts until butter is melted.
Fold in coconut; set aside.
Prepare meringue.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling, sealing it well to the crust.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Layer bean dip in dish.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together and layer that on bean dip.
Chop onions and tomatoes layer on sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over this and any optional ingredients you like.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: fried chicken with herbs
directions: Place the chicken pieces in a bowl with 1 cup of the buttermilk. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or up to 18 hours. Preheat an oven to 400°.

title: mock swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Form meatballs about spoon size. Set aside.
Put tomato soup and chicken with rice soup in large frypan.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Cook 30 minutes. Serve over potatoes or eat plain.

title: 30 minute shrimp and sausage gumbo
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Stir in flour.
Cook 4 minutes or until golden brown, stirring frequently. Add green pepper, onion, celery and garlic; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add turkey sausage, tomatoes, broth, okra, bay leaf and thyme; stir until well blended.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp; cook 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Remove bay leaf; discard.
Serve shrimp mixture over rice.

title: egg omelette italian
directions: Combine oil, butter, garlic, onion and pepperoni in omelette pan and saute until onion is clear.
Add eggs, top with cheese, cover and cook over low heat until firm.
Top with marinara sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Have bacon real crispy and hot dogs let cool and then cut up. Chop onion and cheese.
Pour all other ingredients together.
Stir all together and bake for 20 minutes.

title: buttercream icing(this is the icing used in cake decorating classes)
directions: Icing is right consistency when you are able to squeeze it through the tip easily and it retains its shape.
Consistency of soft putty.
Mix slowly until smooth, but do not overmix as it will form air bubbles.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Take a small portion of cheese mixture in palm of hand, place olive in center and gently press dough around it and roll into ball.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cabbage deluxe
directions: Cut up 1 head cabbage.
Put into pot with very little water. Add margarine, salt and pepper; cook until tender.
Boil pasta; drain.
Combine with cabbage.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Seed peppers and cut in chunks.
Chop in blender with 1/2 cup vinegar.

title: potato balls(a good way to use leftover mashed potatoes)
directions: Divide potatoes into 6 equal parts; press a cheese cube into each.
Shape into a ball.
Dip potato balls into melted margarine; then into corn flake crumbs.
Place in a shallow baking dish. Bake in preheated 400°
oven for 10 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice, 2 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch. Cook until thickened.
Set aside to cool.

title: hot shrimp salad
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen; rinse and drain.
If large, cut in half.
Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart baking dish, or into 6 well-greased ramekins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine potato chips and cheese; mix well.
Sprinkle over shrimp mixture. Return to the oven and continue baking for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange slice-applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add applesauce, chopped nuts and raisins.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in orange slice candies, cut in pieces.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 7 minutes.
When syrup cools, add juice mixture.
Add 3 quarts ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: spiced chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, using electric mixer, cream butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Alternately add dry ingredients with milk, beginning and ending with flour, using one third of the milk at a time.
Beat until well blended after each addition.
Pour batter in floured and greased pans.
Bake until a cake tester inserted into the center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice
zucchini 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; turn
in
flour.
Fry on each side until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
In
same
pan, fry onions and peppers; add to this tomato paste and water.
Arrange zucchini in baking dish; pour the tomato
mixture
over the zucchini and sprinkle with cheese. Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk. Combine with other ingredients and stir lightly and quickly.
Turn onto floured surface and knead gently 20 to 30 times.
Roll out or pat to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 1-inch biscuit cutter. Brush each biscuit with oil or butter.
Place biscuit on top of each biscuit on ungreased sheet.
Cover and let rise for 2 hours. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Mix with crushed cookies.
Pat in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine the flour and the sugar.
In a heavy saucepan combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in the bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using a wood spoon or high speed on electric mixer.
Pour into a well buttered 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies test done in the center.
While brownies bake, prepare the frosting.
In a saucepan combine butter, cocoa and milk.
Heat to boiling; keep stirring.
Mix in the powdered sugar and vanilla until frosting is smooth.

title: strawberry pudding cake
directions: Arrange four 1-inch slices of pound cake in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Pile strawberries on top of cake.
Pour pudding over strawberries.
Whip cream with sugar and vanilla.
Top cake and refrigerate.

title: country peanut brittle
directions: Butter	2
large baking sheets;
set aside.
Butter the sides of	a
heavy 3 quart saucepan.
In the saucepan combine sugar, corn syrup, water and the 1/4 cup butter or margarine. Cook
over medium-high
heat
to boiling, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugar.
This should take about 5 minutes.
Avoid splashing mixture on sides of pan.	Carefully
clip
candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook over medium-low
heat,
stirring occasionally, until thermometer registers 275°,
soft
crack stage.
Mixture should boil at a moderate, steady
rate
over entire surface.
Reaching soft crack stage should take 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sour cream squash casserole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook squash until limp and tender; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tasty baked cod(low-fat)
directions: Place the fish in an oiled baking dish.
Season it with lemon juice and pepper.
Place the tomato slices on the fish and sprinkle with the green pepper and onion.
In a small bowl, combine the bread crumbs, basil and oil; spread the crumb mixture evenly over the tomatoes.
Bake the fish, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cooked dressing
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add butter; remove from heat.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat milk and egg yolks.
Mix flour with sugar.
Add all to milk and cook over low heat until thick.
Beat egg whites for top of pie.
Put into baked pie crust. Brown top.

title: curry lentil soup
directions: Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: baked chicken romanesque
directions: In shallow baking pan, place chicken.
Brush with oil. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper on chicken.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from oven and set aside.

title: fresh apple cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; add the apples. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to apple mixture. Mix thoroughly (batter will be thick). Add nuts and mix again.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch square pan, loaf pan or Bundt pan. Bake 90 minutes at 325°. Test cake with toothpick.
(Can add 3/4 cup raisins, if desired.)

title: swiss steak in foil
directions: Tear off foot length of foil.
Fold shiny side in.
Combine catsup and flour and spoon half of it in center of foil.
Place steak on top. Season with salt and cover meat with onion and remaining catsup and flour mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Fold foil over and seal securely.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon in Dutch oven until crisp; remove and drain on paper towels.
Set aside.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes
or until potatoes are tender.
Add corn and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes about 9 cups soup.

title: fast and easy asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus spears and place in Pammed ovenproof dish. Pour over this 1 can cream of asparagus soup (not diluted).
Top with a light sprinkling of crushed cheese crackers; can add sliced almonds, also.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm and crumble in the yeast.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down and place in Sally Lunn ring mold or tube pan.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(I cook at 325°.)

title: deep sea wedges
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut tops off and remove core.
Mix cheese, dressing and crab meat.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut peppers into wedges.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat in pot.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine in separate pot and mix well.
Set aside.
Press half of this mixture into the bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together. Stir into dry ingredients. Add enough flour to prevent dough from sticking. Turn out on board and knead until dough is workable. Roll out and cut in small biscuits. Dip in melted butter. Stack one on top of the other (using two). Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cold-oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla or other flavoring.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Start in COLD oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean and cake begins to pull away from pan.
Let cool a few minutes and turn on rack to finish cooling.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix in flour and sugar; add eggs, then add milk.
Stir constantly.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with water and margarine cut into water.
First layer, in 13 x 9-inch pan, the dressing mix.

title: tamale casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups salsa; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 5 minutes.
In meantime, mix together cornbread mix according to package directions.
Mix in 1 cup cheese and black olives.
Pour mixture into 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Spoon hamburger into center of cornbread mixture, showing on sides.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with remaining cheese and salsa and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sun-drop pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and Crisco well, then add eggs one at a time.
Then add flour, Sun-Drop, vanilla and lemon flavoring. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: the tarson taco salad recipe
directions: Brown beef.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sit down and enjoy.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, celery, onion, pickle and pimento together. Combine a couple of heaping tablespoons of Miracle Whip with equal amounts of Cooked Dressing and toss vegetables.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and water.
Beat until smooth.
Add soup and gelatin powder.
Heat until warm.
Do not boil!
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with crackers or nachos.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks gradually and beat well.
Add flour and salt mixture alternately with evaporated milk.
Mix on low speed while adding vanilla and mix.
Pour filling into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake approximately one hour at 300° or until set in center.
If not brown enough, turn up to 350° for a few minutes.

title: kit-kat pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Reserve 1/4 cup of candy bars, stir remaining candy bars into pudding mixture. Put in pie crust.
Sprinkle top with remaining candy bars, drizzle with chocolate syrup and refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread beans in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Brown beef; drain and mix with taco seasoning.
Spread mixture over beans. Top with corn chips.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through (about 30 minutes).
Top with cheese; return to oven just until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: pink fluff
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, melted butter and chopped nuts; mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove, stir and return to oven to bake another 10 minutes. Remove half of the crumbs to be used for topping.

title: ham-and-eggs crescent pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press 1/2 inch up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower rack of oven; set aside.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 days, turning over several times.
Before cooking, remove meat and wash off spices.
Strain marinade, discarding spices and vegetables.

In 1 tablespoon Crisco, sear meat in frying pan. Roast in roaster with 2/3 cup of the juice for about 2 hours (baste occasionally). When meat is nearly done, sprinkle 1/3 cup brown sugar over it and roast 10 more minutes.
In a pan, thicken remaining marinade.
Put in 4 gingersnaps (they will dissolve). Add 1/3 cup flour and blend in.
Cook until mixture thickens. Pour over meat in roaster. Blend with roasting juices.
Roast 1/2 hour more until gravy is creamy and thick.
Remove meat and add 1/2 cup red wine to gravy.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up ends of broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix other ingredients; pour over broccoli and cauliflower.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni in 1/2 teaspoon of salt in boiling water.
Drain and rinse.
Chop eggs, celery, onions and pickles.
Drain and rinse shrimp.
Mix all and add salt, pepper and mayonnaise.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and
sugar; cut shortening into mixture.
Add eggs, mix.
Combine other ingredients in any order.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg, vinegar and water.
Add shortening to dry mixture and mix well.
Add liquid and mix.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Add eggs and mix until smooth and fluffy.
Add applesauce.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix the ingredients all together.
Roll dough into strips as thin as you like.

title: cobbler
directions: Oil
Dutch
oven
well.
Line the oven with foil.
Pour the pie filling and spread it evenly on the foil bottom.
Make the cake mix and pour it evenly over the pie filling.
Mix the nuts and
oil and spread evenly on top.	Cover and bake for 25 minutes.

title: country grits and sausage
directions: Bring water to a boil; stir in grits.
Return to a boil; reduce heat and cook 4 minutes and continue to stir.
Combine grits and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine eggs, milk, thyme and garlic powder in small bowl; mix well.
Add a small amount of hot grits mixture to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Stir egg mixture into remaining hot grits.
Add sausage and stir well. Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tikka
directions: Place the ginger and garlic, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 1/4 cup of the yoghurt in a food processor and puree until smooth. Scrape the puree into a bowl with the remaining 3/4 cup yoghurt, 3 tablespoons oil, the chili powder and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir well. Cut each halved chicken breast crosswise into 3 pieces.
Add the chicken to the yoghurt mixture and toss to coat.
Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed, except instead of adding water, add broth chicken was cooked in (plus add water to needed amount). Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and pat dry mushrooms; cut off stems (save).
Saute caps in butter; pat dry or drain.
Cook sausage (break up); cut up stems and cook with sausage.
Add cream cheese, cut up in chunks to melt and add sausage.
Stuff mushrooms, sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: party cheese cakes
directions: You will need 12 foil-liners for muffin tin.

title: rice delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add large container of Cool Whip.
Let set overnight.

title: quick homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, pudding and evaporated milk.
Add fruit.
Pour into ice cream freezer can.
Add milk.
Stir.
Omit fruit for vanilla ice cream.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together the first five (5) ingredients.
Add the next four (4) ingredients;
mixing well after each addition.

title: potato soup
directions: Add all ingredients together in pot. Heat over medium heat for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sauce for broccoli or cauliflower
directions: Mix together and heat in microwave or stir and cook on top of stove.

title: beef and beer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven, brown beef in 1 tablespoon oil, remove from pan and set aside.
In same Dutch oven, saute celery, onion and garlic in remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Add beef stew, beer, pumpernickel crumbs and carrots.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Put 1 teaspoon soda in each can of soup and mix.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured pan; bake at 350° until done.

title: easy cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
These can be bar cookies or rolled into walnut size balls for baking.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian easter pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut up all lunchmeats into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl; pour into pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 13 x 9 pan.
Let cool. Mix together milk, instant pudding and cream cheese. Spread over cooled cake.
Spread drained pineapple on top.
Smooth Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and garlic powder in skillet.
Cook on medium heat until meat is brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies, pepper, taco, seasoning mix, salt and chili powder.
Cook mixture 5 minutes.
Cut each tortilla in 8 pieces.
Place half of pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with meat mixture.
Place remaining pieces on top of meat.

title: double cheese meat roll
directions: Combine beef, egg, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well and shape into flat 10 x 12-inch wax paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Roll up like jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in shallow dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain excess fat. Pour remaining sauce over roll and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: lithuanian beet pickled eggs
directions: Put grated potatoes in a cheesecloth bag.
Squeeze, letting liquid drip into pan.
Let stand undisturbed, until starch settles.
Drain off liquid.
Add starch to grated potatoes.
Add salt and mix thoroughly.
Form mixture into balls the size of a walnut or smaller.
Drop into salted, boiling water.
Cook 20 minutes.
These dumplings may be served with crispy bacon or sour cream.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour and mix.
Add potato chips.
Drop a teaspoon dough on greased cookie sheet.
If you want, you can roll dough (a teaspoon) into crushed potato chips instead of adding chips to dough.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: hamburg skillet casserole
directions: Melt fat in skillet; add ground beef and salt; brown lightly, stirring frequently.
Mix parsley, onion soup mix, water and carrots.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat; cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add noodles and frozen peas.
Cook until noodles are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream molasses, margarine, honey and egg.
Stir flours with baking powder, salt and spices.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with boiling water.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir to mix.
Add sugar, shortening, butter, eggs, egg whites, extract, cream and coconut.
Beat mixture 1 minute, then high for 2 minutes.
The batter will be thick and fluffy.
Spoon into pan, bake 1 hour.
When done, turn cake onto a large plate.
Let cool slightly before slicing.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Puree frozen raspberries and their syrup in a food processor or blender.
To eliminate the seeds, push the raspberries through a sieve, mashing down on the puree with a spoon.
Discard the seeds.

title: potato supreme
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet.
Add beef and garlic.
Saute until browned.
Remove
meat
and
add onion and green pepper. Saute two minutes.
Return
meat
and
add tomatoes to skillet with bouillon beef cube.
Simmer (15 to 20 minutes) for round. Blend remaining ingredients and
add to meat mixture, stirring constantly, for a couple
of
minutes until thick.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In small saucepan combine salad dressing, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over low heat about 3 minutes or until just heated.
Stir in lemon peel and lemon juice.
Serve over vegetables.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased pan. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown in frying pan the first 4 ingredients in a small amount of corn oil.
Now, mix the last 4 ingredients together in a different bowl.
Mix meat mixture and tomato mixture; salt and pepper.
Put into casserole dish and top with grated cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ice water chocolate cake
directions: Cream until fluffy first three ingredients.
Add eggs and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat dry ingredients and creamed mixture alternately with 1 1/2 cups ice water.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.
Use chocolate or vanilla icing to top cake before serving.

title: apples and cheese
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour and cheese cut into small chunks to make a coarse dough. Put apples in a casserole dish. Spoon dough over apples.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together except margarine and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
