Dot with margarine. Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°
and bake for 50 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine, milk and flour; set aside.
Mix vegetables, chicken and soups.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour flour mixture over this and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Cut crust from bread slices; cut into 5 fingers.
Place fingers over fruit.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs and butter, pour over fruit and bread.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: * no frost oatmeal cake *
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Add the brown sugar, white sugar and butter or oleo to oatmeal and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: red cabbage
directions: Saute onion chopped in margarine.
Add chopped cabbage and stir and saute for 5 minutes.
Add chopped apples and vinegar. Add sugar or honey to taste.
Cover and cook slowly, stirring once in a while for 45 minutes or 1 hour.
Salt, if desired.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Pour milk over bread until soft.
Combine all ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can mix the night before.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large fry pan.
Add tomatoes, enchilada sauce, olives, salt, garlic and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Saute tortillas in and drain on paper towels.
Then cut in half.
Beat cottage cheese with egg. Spread 1/3 of meat mix in a shallow 3-quart casserole.
Top with half of Jack cheese and 1/2 of cottage cheese mix, then tortilla halves.
Repeat layering ending
with meat last.
Top with Cheddar cheese and chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked rice pilaf
directions: Saute garlic and rice in butter until pale yellow.
Add the bouillon.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add cheese and stir with a fork until cheese is melted and rice is fluffy.

title: economical gold cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure and add baking powder and sift together 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly. Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour alternately, a small amount at a time.
Add flavoring.
Beat well.
Bake in greased pan 8 x 8 x 2-inch in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.
Frost with your choice.
For a large cake, double recipe.

title: no fry french fries
directions: Mix together 1 tablespoon of Cajun spice with egg whites in a bowl.
Mix together potatoes and mixture.
Lightly coat a pan with Pam.
Put potatoes and rest of mixture into pan.
Lightly spray top of potatoes with Pam.
Put into oven at 400°.
Finished when brown, 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn every 6 to 8 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dates, soda and butter in boiling water; cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in buttered and floured bread pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes on High and 10 to 15 minutes on Bake in microwave or bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: quick and easy texas brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee (or water) and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
You may substitute 2 teaspoons vinegar or lemon juice into 1/2 cup milk for buttermilk.
Mix well with wooden spoon or mixer.
Pour into a well buttered jelly roll pan or sheet cake pan.	Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together first seven ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: famous blueberry salad
directions: Put gelatin in bowl with 2 cups boiling water. Let cool. Add pineapple and juice from blueberries. Allow to partially set, then whip up and add blueberries and nuts. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into a long glass dish or individual cups. Chill.

title: my mom's chew charlies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk, cocoa and salt.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
(If batter becomes too stiff, add a few drops of milk.)
Drop in tablespoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare 9 to 10-inch pie plate by spraying Pam to coat, then open biscuits and line pie dish by separating them into sections so that bottom and sides are covered.
Set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat. add water, potatoes and seasoning mix. Simmer covered for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir. Uncover and cook until excess water is evaporated.

title: sun-dried tomato and basil spread
directions: Chop all ingredients in processor to coarse paste. Season with salt and pepper. Spread on pita or bread slices.

title: baked lima beans in sour cream
directions: Cook lima beans; drain and rinse.
In a small bowl mix remaining ingredients until well blended, add to the beans.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave fresh cream-style corn
directions: Shuck, silk and wash corn.
Split each row of kernels with sharp knife.
Carefully slice just the tips of corn into a large bowl.
Using dull side of knife, run it down the cob to extract all the milky pulp from corn.
Put cut off corn into deep microwave dish with butter, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High for 10 minutes.
Add milk and arrowroot or cornstarch.
If you like it thicker, add more.
Cook on 70% power for 6 to 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until desired consistency.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Place all ingredients in a very large bowl or kettle.
Stir until well blended.
Store in airtight containers or pack in small gift containers.
To serve, add hot water.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding avocado last.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Place lettuce (shredded) on bottom and a scoop of chicken salad.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Combine chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour above mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated. Shake with powdered sugar in resealable plastic bag until well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add rice and saute, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Place in roasting pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over rice. Cover lightly.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Fluff with fork before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix together flour and dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Stir in pecans and poppy seed.
Pour batter into three (8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Gradually brush on the cakes.
Let cool completely on wire racks.
Refrigerate up to a week or freeze up to 3 months.

title: south of the border steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly batter meat in mixture.
In frying pan, brown meat, garlic and bell pepper. Remove meat; place in tortillas.
Roll up and place in baking dish side by side.
Pour picante sauce, mushrooms, bell pepper and garlic mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, then sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serve with sour cream on top, rice on the side.

title: elaine's pork chops deluxe
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of pork chops and brown in pan. Remove and put in baking dish.
Remove fat and add the water to the pan.

title: lazy boy pie
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish at 425°.
Cook fruit with sugar.
Mix flour, milk and 1 cup sugar.
Pour in dish.
Then pour fruit over that.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato soup
directions: Chop onion and celery.
Peel and dice potatoes into a pan with 1 quart water, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes; add 1 cup milk. In a shaker, mix flour with other cup of milk.
Add to soup. Stir constantly until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Add butter and parsley before serving.
Add egg, if desired.

title: irish boiled dinner
directions: Trim fat from beef brisket.
Place in an 8-quart Dutch oven. Add beer, onion (sliced thin), bay leaf, peppercorns, bouillon cubes, salt and water.
Heat until boiling.
Cover closely and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cook beets separately (tops optional). Place cooked brisket on a large platter to cool.
Add cabbage, carrots and potatoes to the stock and bring to boil; simmer until done (about 30 minutes covered).
Cut brisket thin.
Serve slices of brisket with the vegetables from broth.
Pass the horseradish and use beets as a side dish.

title: spicy beef and veggie soup
directions: Heat oil in skillet until very hot.
Add meat cubes and brown well.
Transfer beef to crock-pot and add onion, garlic, potatoes, carrots and 1/2 bottle of each V-8 juice.
Simmer on low for 6 to 8 hours until meat is very tender.
For last 1/2 hour of cooking, turn heat to medium-high and add remaining ingredients, except cilantro.
Reserve cilantro to sprinkle on top of soup just before serving.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Pour milk over wafers, set aside.
Cream together sugar, eggs and butter.
Add wafer mix, flavoring, coconut and nuts.
Cook in a tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cornish game hens
directions: In Ziploc plastic bag, pour bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and ginger.
Pour lemon juice over split Cornish hens. Put 1/2 hen in bag with bread crumbs.
Shake.
Place in foil covered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix pink lemonade according to directions on the can. Add all other juices and stir well. Put in punch bowl with ice cubes and just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: pizza bread
directions: Brown sausages.
When somewhat cool, add 1 beaten egg.
Cool some more and then spread on rolled out dough.
Roll up and fold down edges.
Beat one more egg to brush on top of each loaf.
Put cheese on each loaf before rolling it up.
Bake at 350° until well browned.

title: janie's hamburger and vegetable stew
directions: Cook hamburger meat in large pot with water until completely done; usually takes 45 minutes.
While meat is cooking, wash and cut green beans, onions, carrots, celery and cabbage.
When meat is ready, drain well and add all vegetables to meat.
Fill with water to cover vegetables.
Add beef bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Cook on high for 30 minutes and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: grandpere's maple syrup dumplings
directions: Heat the maple syrup to a boil.
Combine eggs (beaten until fluffy), flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling syrup.
Dumplings will bob up; allow to cook for 5 minutes.
Delicious as is or with cream.

title: pecan tassies(from pampered chef)
directions: Let margarine and cream cheese soften to room temperature. Mix together.
Add flour and mix to form a soft dough.
Chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Form the dough into 30 walnut-sized balls.
Place each ball of dough in the center of a mini-muffin cup.
Dip a tart shaper in flour, then press into the dough to make perfect tarts.
Pierce the shells with a fork and bake empty at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or fill unbaked tarts with pecan tassie filling and bake as directed.

title: caramel devil's food cake
directions: Melt chocolate and caramel chips in double boiler; cool slightly.
Cream butter.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in caramel-chocolate mixture.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating smooth after each addition.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy breezy crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Moisten with oil and milk.
Chill.
Roll into one crust.
As a rule, one needs at least 1 1/3 cups flour for an 8-inch pan.

title: hot pepper cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Stir in mayonnaise, peppers, onion and pepper juice.
Put in containers and store in refrigerator.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar, then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in crushed crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a well-buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish or cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Spread cooled pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: guilt free heavenly pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package using low-fat milk. Mix pudding, sour cream, pineapple and sweetener.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with kiwi fruit. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix cookie mixture according to directions.
Roll out and bake on pizza pan.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and add sugar gradually and cream.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cookies dough.
Put sliced strawberries on top of mixture.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, eggs, vanilla flavoring and flour together. Cook in top of double boiler on low heat, stirring to keep from sticking, until it gets thick.
Put layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of 2-quart Pyrex dish and then a layer of sliced bananas. Pour half of pudding over this.
Make another layer of wafers and bananas, then pudding.
Beat egg whites and put meringue on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together.
Stir in noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in oblong pan and spread evenly.
Dump pie filling and spread evenly and then add the dry cake mix.
Cut butter into slices and completely cover the mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Place brisket in seasoned (Pam) pan.
Sprinkle with seasonings and pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Cover pan with foil. Marinate overnight.

title: barbie's apple butter country ribs
directions: Place ribs in large dutch oven, add water to cover.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Drain well; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Combine apple butter and remaining ingredients in a saucepan; stir well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Coat ribs generously with apple butter sauce, place on a cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour in 250-300° oven.
Baste occasionally with sauce.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Arrange rice in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle soup over rice. Saute chicken in margarine until brown.
Arrange chicken on top of rice and soup.
Saute celery and carrot in margarine.
Sprinkle vegetables on chicken.
Pour water over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered with foil.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine the soup in a bowl, mixing well.
Add onion (chopped), if desired.
Pour mixture over potatoes in a baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: potato "souffle"
directions: Peel and cook the potatoes until tender.
Mash until smooth. Combine potatoes with sour cream, margarine, soup, onions and cheese.
Add some salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in casserole.
May be frozen before cooking, if necessary.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking powder into mixing bowl. Beat whites and yolks separately.
Add milk to yolks and beat. Add this to sifted flour, beating until very smooth, then add melted butter and stiffly beaten egg whites.
I sometimes add some applesauce or mashed banana.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans.
Using a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, granulated sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda, shortening, milk, eggs and chocolate chips.
Blend 1 1/2 minutes on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 40-45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes our clean.
Cool. Place butterscotch filling between layers, use chocolate chip glaze to top cake and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: kahlua hummers
directions: In a blender, combine kahlua, light rum and ice cream. Blend briefly and serve.
By the pitcher:
6-oz. Kahlua, 6-oz. light rum, 2-1/2 c. ice cream.

title: cream cheese flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine sugar and water in a medium saucepan, cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 3 to 4 minutes or until dissolved.

Increase heat to medium-high, boil without stirring for about 15 minutes or until caramel colored. Quickly pour over bottom and sides of 12 six ounce custard cups (if syrup hardens, soften over low heat).
Place evaporated milk, sweetened condensed milk, cream cheese, butter, eggs and vanilla extract in blender container, cover and blend well.
Pour mixture into prepared custard cups.
Arrange in one or two large pans, pour hot water in pans to 1 inch depth (water bath).
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Run knife around rims and gently shake to loosen.
Invert into serving dish.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla. Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter; sift dry ingredients.
Stir in creamed mixture. Form into tiny balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with fork to make crisscrosses.
Dough may also be rolled and cut, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Yields about 8 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy lasagna squares
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer Parmesan and cottage cheese.
Mix beef, oregano, salt, pepper, paste and 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon evenly into casserole.
Beat milk, egg and Bisquick.
Pour over beef.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: mom's italian chicken soup
directions: Bring water and bouillon cubes to boil for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature.
Add chicken, onion, celery, tomatoes and spices; cook over low-medium heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove chicken from soup; remove all meat from bones.
Return chicken to soup.
Boil macaroni until done.
Spoon orzo and soup into bowls.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Wash raisins; drain and place in saucepan.
Add water and cloves; simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Stir into raisin mixture.
Simmer and stir about 3 minutes or until sauce is thick.
Add the butter and vinegar. Simmer about 1 or 2 minutes.

title: luncheon salad(serves 12)
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, celery, pineapple and 1 1/2 cups slivered almonds. Mix mayonnaise with curry powder and soy sauce. Add to meat mixture. Chill several hours. Spoon onto lettuce leaves. Sprinkle remaining toasted almonds and garnish with litchi nuts or pineapple.

title: cream cheese tortillas
directions: Mix and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and chill.
Cut into quarters.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: never-fail corn bread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, eggs, sugar, milk and shortening in bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until mixed well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in slow oven at 300°.

title: tom tiddle gingerbread
directions: Place in mixing bowl the molasses, brown sugar and shortening. Mix together and add the remaining ingredients.
Beat to mix well.
Pour into greased and floured square cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: solid gold brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate morsels in double boiler or microwave. Stir in margarine.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup margarine in bowl.
Mix well and pat into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine sugar and remaining 1/2 cup margarine in large mixing bowl.
Beat until light, then add eggs, then beat until light and fluffy.
Spread over crust. Then add bananas and top with pineapple.
Cover with whipped topping and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Garnish with cherries.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken.
Mix poppy seed and crackers; sprinkle on top. Pour butter over all.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off all grease.
Add taco seasoning, water and beans; cook 10 minutes.
Add green chili peppers.
Layer in a casserole dish.
Put tortillas on bottom, then bean mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: english pea salad
directions: Place well drained peas, onion, pickle, green pepper, pimento, celery and cheese in a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Toss with salad dressing.
Garnish top with paprika.
Chill for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
In another bowl, mix everything well.
Do not precook rice; mix in raw.
Stir in tomatoes with juice; mix very well.
Pour mixture over butter in dish and cover.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: aunt irene's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and part of the milk in a saucepan. Then add sugar mixed with cocoa and cornstarch. Stir the mixture very well. Add remaining milk, vanilla and butter and mix well. Cook until thickened. Pour chocolate mixture into a baked pie shell. Cover with meringue if desired.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika and pepper.
Brown rice and onion in margarine.
Spread rice mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered baking dish.
Place chicken on top of rice and pour the broth on top.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: baked corned beef
directions: Parboil corned beef for 15 minutes.
Place roast in roasting pan and cover with the orange juice.
Generously pierce corned beef with the cloves.
Add bay leaves to roasting pan.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Cut against the grain.
Great served with boiled red potatoes and cabbage.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and salt.
Scald milk until crinkly film forms on top.
Stir in egg mixture gradually.
Add vanilla.
Pour into custard cups or baking dish; set in pan of hot water.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove from pan of water. Serve cool or chilled.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Roll chicken in flour, saute until golden brown.
Mix soup, onions and seasonings in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in the water, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour rice from the box into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Stir all but 1/3 cup soup mixture into rice.
Top with chicken, pour on the remainder of the soup mixture, cover.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° or until the chicken is done.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch casserole dish, layer broccoli, chicken, bread crumbs and cheese.
Mix gravy, milk and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: meat roll
directions: Combine and mix first eight ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat mixture to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham atop meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using paper to lift; seal edges and ends.
Place roll, seam side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° until done, about 1 1/4 hours.
Center will be pink due to ham.
Place cheese strips over top of roll; return to oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Makes 8 good servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables until tender, but still firm.
Drain. In a large bowl, combine cooked vegetables, onion, celery salt, soup and stuffing mix.
Place in casserole dish.
Dot with butter; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 8 minutes more.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and jello. Cook for five minutes. Chill. Add buttermilk, nuts, and Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into 9x13 inch dish. Chill over night.

title: fruit snow
directions: In 2-quart, nonmetallic container, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; freeze.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Melt butter; mix in flour, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Roll small pieces between hands to form fingers.
Bake on ungreased pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Roll in xxxx sugar.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in two 8-inch pans.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel fresh yams and cut lengthwise.
Roll in flour while damp. Cover each layer well with brown sugar.
Pour water around edges of dish.
Cut up stick of butter.
Place on top of yams.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until tender.
Take off lid and brown the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: four cup salad
directions: Combine and congeal in refrigerator.

title: sharla's mom's chocolate cake
directions: In a large saucepan, cook pudding mix and milk until thickened.
Remove from heat and add cake mix.
Mix thoroughly. Place mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Scatter chocolate chips across top of cake mixture.
Add nuts, too, if so desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: great chips and cheese
directions: Put the cheese, beans and oleo in crock-pot and heat until melted and hot.
Stir often and make sure mixture doesn't burn. Pour over tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: low sodium orange glazed chicken
directions: Sprinkle cut-up chicken with seasoning salt and pepper.

In a skillet over medium heat, in margarine, saute chicken until golden. Add oregano, orange peel, orange juice, corn syrup and water. Cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until tender, basting several times.
Use parsley sprigs as garnish.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving equals 88 mg sodium.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Cut tortillas in quarters.
Line casserole with tortillas; layer remaining ingredients and grated cheese.

title: philly cheese deer sandwiches
directions: Take steak buns and spread Miracle Whip, lettuce and tomatoes on them; set aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drop deer in, stirring, about 5 to 8 minutes. Add diced onions and green peppers.
Cook about 5 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; cover until cheese is melted.
Put on prepared buns; salt and pepper to taste.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar. Continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Chill about one hour.
Shape dough into balls 3/4-inch in diameter.
Dip into slightly beaten egg white, then into nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press hole in center of each cookie with floured finger.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with tinted creamy butter frosting.

title: guilt free spicy cranberry dip
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cranberry sauce with all ingredients, except fruit and sausage.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve warm with orange, pineapple and turkey sausage.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add granulated sugar gradually.
Blend in bitter chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition, about 5 minutes, until firm.
Put into prepared crust and garnish with chopped nuts and cream.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa in an 8 x 8-inch pan using a fork.
Make a "well" in 3 places in the mixture.
Add an equal amount of the vinegar and oil each into these wells.
Add water and mix with a fork until well blended.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked squash sacramento
directions: Mash squash; stir in butter, sugar, cream, seasonings and eggs.
Fold in part of almonds, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining almonds.
Bake in 375° (moderately hot) oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Cream together cheese and oleo that is room temperature.
Add flour and salt and mix well.
Add Tabasco sauce.
Add Rice Krispies and mix with hands.
Make into marble size balls and press down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes. Cool. Add juice and bananas. Freeze for 2 hours before serving. Take from freezer and add ginger ale.

title: cauliflower broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain.
While still hot, add cubed cheese and 1/4 cup of margarine.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and 1/4 cup of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot nut mix
directions: Heat red peppers in oil for 1 minute.
Crush garlic and add to oil.
Add all peanuts and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add chili powder.
Drain on paper towels.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on greased grill over medium-hot coals (coals will have slight glow) or rack of broiler pan 5 to 7 inches from heat.
Brush with 1/2 of the mixture.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining mixture.
Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: indian puddinga yankee favorite!
directions: In a large saucepan, scald the milk.
Using a wire whisk, gradually stir in the cornmeal.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon, about 10 minutes.
Stir in the butter or margarine; remove from heat.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, mayonnaise, onion and celery and set aside.
Mix together 2 eggs, broth, butter and stuffing mix.
In a casserole dish, put one layer of stuffing mix and then the chicken mixture and top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Beat together eggs and milk and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. When ready to cook, add cream of chicken soup over top and cook at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika to add color.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Brown sausage and drain off excess grease.
Saute together the onions, pepper, celery and sausage.
Combine sauteed mixture to rice mixture.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add rice, cheese, soup, milk and water to onion.
Stir.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee dessert
directions: Whip Dream Whip.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Mix together. Put on crackers; cool and add pie mix.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage, celery and onions; drain.
Cook 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
This can be made a day ahead.
Serves 6 to 8 easily.

title: strawberry-fig jam
directions: Combine the ingredients; bring to a boil.
Lower the heat; continue to boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized, hot jars.
Place lids on and process for 5 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yields 6 half pints.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Lay flat on baking sheet and bake according to package directions.
Combine the cream cheese and powdered Ranch dressing.
Spread on cooled crust.
Chop vegetables and sprinkle over dressing mix (any vegetables can be used, whatever your preference is).
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Cut into small pieces.
Enjoy.

title: special brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.
May serve plain or sprinkle with powdered sugar and frost.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, saute mushrooms and onions in 3 tablespoons butter until golden brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining butter.
Brown meat on all sides, 15 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Pour over meat.
Add tomato paste, mustard and salt.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes, until tender.

title: grilled catfish
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Sprinkle lemon juice and seasoning mixture over both sides of fish.
Spray wire fish basket with cooking spray.
Grill fish in covered grill over medium coals for 7 to 10 minutes per side or until the fish flakes easily.
Garnish with lemon.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a 1 quart pyrex dish, mix cream cheese, crabmeat (drained and flaked), green onion, milk, parsley, lemon juice, and Worcestershire Sauce.
After blending, cover with plastic wrap and microwave on high for 4 minutes-stirring after 2 minutes.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans according to package; drain well.
Add mushrooms and onion to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir over heat 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add bacon, beans and pepper.
Mix.
Spoon into a 2-quart dish.

title: broccoli casserole(6 servings)
directions: Toss croutettes stuffing mix with melted margarine.
Set aside for topping.
Prepare broccoli according to package directions, cooking until almost tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain.
Set aside.

title: lone star chili
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat with onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and continue to simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve topped with Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Enjoy!
Hot!

title: japanese salad
directions: Combine chicken, lettuce, green onion, almonds and poppy seed. Meanwhile, mix dressing in salad bottle.
Mix sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil.
Pour over salad.
Top with noodles.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy; add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough (1 1/2-inch balls), about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheets before transferring to wire racks to cool thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients and add dry mixture gradually into creamed mixture.
Blend well. Roll into 1-inch balls and flatten out with bottom of glass.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes until edges are lightly brown.
Frost and decorate when cool.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Rinse chicken pieces.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Dip each piece of chicken in 1/4 cup butter, then bread crumb mixture. Arrange chicken in a shallow roasting pan, making sure not to overlap pieces.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until browned as desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: good-n-rich
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Bring to a boil shortening, raisins, salt and sugar.
Let cool.
Sift in mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Wash, stem and reserve skins from grapes.
Cook pulp for 5 minutes; press through sieve to remove seeds.
Combine pulp with grape skins and add lemon juice.
Mix the sugar, flour and salt and add to grape mixture.

title: honey glazed brandied carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until they are tender; drain. In a skillet, place carrots and remaining ingredients; cook and stir until carrots are glazed and glossy.
Serves 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add paste to batter.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl. Add to batter.
Beat well.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in an uncovered roasting pan.
Mix ingredients in bowl and pour over ribs.
Baste and turn halfway through cooking. Bake at 325° for about 2 hours or until meat is cooked.

title: quick tomato soup
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour and powders in saucepan until smooth.
Gradually stir in tomato juice and sugar. Warm over low-medium heat until heated through.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and dice.
Dice and add pickles, celery, eggs and onion; mix together.
Add salt, pepper and salad dressing; sprinkle with paprika.
Cut egg on top in circles.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Cook diced potatoes 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and spread on towel to cool.
After cooling, place potatoes in a mixing bowl.
Sprinkle onion and celery on top of potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup.
Gradually add milk and egg, mixing well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits as directed on box.
Add oleo, eggs, seasoning and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 250° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: turkey sandwich mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in microwave 45 minutes on Medium-high.
Serve on hot buns.
Can be kept hot in slow cooker. Can be frozen and reheated (preferably in slow cooker).

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine the lentils and water in kettle.
Cook for 30 minutes, or until lentils are tender.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until carrots are tender.

title: shrimp, okra and sausage gumbo
directions: To smother okra, slice and saute in oil until brown.
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, seasonings, sausage and water.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes. Add shrimp and green onions.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add chicken.
Stir to coat.
Fry chicken in oil until lightly browned; drain.
Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
To juice, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Stir well.
Combine pineapple juice mixture and next 4 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil.
Stir in pepper and chicken.
Cook until heated.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream, add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 15 minutes prior to serving to partially thaw.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well and mix together (except bananas).
Mix dressing (sour cream and sugar to taste).
Mix fruit, dressing, marshmallows and coconut together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas.

title: pat-a-pizza
directions: Dip fingers into flour to make it easier to pat out biscuits. On a greased cookie sheet, pat to stretch each biscuit to a 4-inch circle.
Spread 1 tablespoon of sauce on each biscuit and top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with a little oregano and garlic powder. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars, vanilla, soda and eggs with oleo.
Add flour. Mix, then add potato chips, nuts and butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mrs. millard luke's chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, currants and nuts.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until pie is set.

title: gratin of artichokes and potatoes
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter; pour into a casserole dish. Slice potatoes and place over onion.
Overlap potatoes with sliced artichokes.
Pour whipping cream over all; top with Parmesan cheese and cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mama's doughnuts
directions: Mix the first five of the ingredients together.
Roll and cut the dough.
Cut out doughnuts and drop into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
The nutmeg and vanilla should be added to the dough mixture according to your taste.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt chips with milk on low heat.
Combine nuts and noodles in large bowl.
Pour melted chips over all; stir.
Drop in balls on waxed paper.
Cool until firm.

title: a friendship recipe
directions: Mix ingredients well. Sprinkle with delight.
Serve with a big smile.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands as it will be stiff. Roll in crescents.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs; mix well.
Form into crust in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and one 9-inch pan.
Cook beef and onions; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, water and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Spread sour cream on crusts.
Fill pies with meat sauce.
Cover with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.
